	<item>
		<title>What is the Payment Process at Paytm?</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?post_type=cma_thread&#038;p=655</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?post_type=cma_thread&#038;p=655</guid>

		<title>Sample Page</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/sample-page/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Oct 2015 10:04:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[creativeslider id="1"]

This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
<blockquote>Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>
...or something like this:
<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>
As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://localhost/wordpress/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paytm set to roll out its hyperlocal business</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/news/paytm-set-to-roll-out-its-hyperlocal-business/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2015 06:21:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=99</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Electronics payments company and marketplace Paytm, run by One97 Communications Ltd, is all set to roll out its hyperlocal business within the next 10 days and expects more than half of its sales to come from this channel by the end of 2016, a senior company executive said.

The hyperlocal offering, to be part of the company’s Paytm mobile wallet offering, will initially focus on food ordering, table bookings, cinema tickets, and deals in the neighbourhood in partnership with multiple firms including BookMyShow (Bigtree Entertainment Pvt. Ltd), PVR, Zomato (Zomato Media Pvt. Ltd) among others, said Vijay Shekhar Sharma, founder and chief executive officer of Paytm.

As hyperlocal becomes the next big thing after the investment frenzy in the e-commerce sector, both businesses and investors are seeking to grab a chunk of that market.

On Wednesday, <i>Mint </i>reported that Japan’s SoftBank Corp., together with Russian entrepreneur and venture capitalist Yuri Milner, are looking to invest close to $120 million in Gurgaon-based hyperlocal delivery startup Grofers, run by Locodel Solutions Pvt. Ltd. The deal-in-the-making was first reported by <i>The Economic Times</i> (though with a different number).

Even large online retailers do not want to miss the hyperlocal rush. Earlier this month, Flipkart launched hyperlocal delivery service Nearby that offers everything from medicines to groceries from stores around users. Snapdeal also bought a minority stake in hyperlocal grocery firm PepperTap, run by Nuvo Logistics Pvt Ltd.

A hyperlocal delivery service is one which provides services or products from local vendors on demand—in a few hours or even quicker.

“In the near future I believe everything will be driven by local delivery… whether it is grocery or electronics, everything will be fulfilled by local stores around you,” said Sharma.

According to Tracxn, a start-up tracker, there are more than 25 food and grocery delivery start-ups operational in India that have together raised more than $160 million over the past 10 months or so. The latest Grofers deal will take that number to a different level.

“Companies are fast realizing that scale lies in cracking the mom-and-pop model, especially in categories such as grocery. If with technology you can get millions of stores online, it is the best way to achieve scale and ensure timely delivery,” said Vineet Toshniwal, managing director at Equirus Capital Pvt. Ltd.

Paytm’s Sharma, it would appear, means everything when he says everything.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Deutsche Bank braces for $7 billion loss, may scrap dividend</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/news/deutsche-bank-braces-for-7-billion-loss-may-scrap-dividend/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2015 06:27:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=102</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>New York: </b>Deutsche Bank AG co-chief executive officer John Cryan unveiled the firm’s biggest quarterly loss in at least a decade and may eliminate a dividend that’s stood since Germany’s postwar reconstruction as he tries to overhaul the firm without asking shareholders for more capital.

Europe’s biggest investment bank expects a third-quarter loss of €6.2 billion ($7 billion) after writing down the value of its two largest divisions and boosting reserves for legal costs. Its American depositary receipts tumbled 6.9% after the disclosure late Wednesday as of 6:36pm in extended trading in New York. Cryan, in a memo to staff, said employees will share some of the burden when the firm sets year- end bonuses.

The charges clear the way for a strategy that Cryan, who became co-CEO in July, is preparing to present later this month as he looks to shore up capital and boost profitability. Spending on regulatory and compliance costs have overwhelmed the firm’s efforts to cut costs.

Cryan “wants to start off with a clean slate for himself and his shareholders,” said David Kass, a professor at the University of Maryland’s Robert H. Smith School of Business. “They’re writing down areas that turned out to be riskier or less profitable than originally expected, essentially saying they’re worth less than before, which would certainly help comparisons in future years look better.”

The firm said it expects to book a €5.8 billion writedown as higher capital requirements reduce the value of its investment bank and it adjusts the estimate of what it will receive in the disposal of its Postbank unit. The Frankfurt-based lender also is adding about €1.2 billion to its litigation reserves.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Market chat: Sensex halts six-day rally on earnings concerns</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/news/market-chat-sensex-halts-six-day-rally-on-earnings-concerns/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2015 07:00:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=106</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Indian stocks dropped as some investors judged the rally in the benchmark index to a six-week high to be excessive before the start of quarterly earnings season next week.

ITC Ltd was the worst performer on the S&amp;P BSE Sensex. Lupin Ltd dropped for a fourth day, the longest losing streak in two months. ICICI Bank Ltd declined the most in a week, pacing losses among non-state lenders. Hindalco Industries Ltd and Vedanta Ltd climbed at least 1% each.

The S&amp;P BSE Sensex fell 0.65%, or 175.63, to 26,860.22 at 11:37am. The gauge has rallied 5.3% since 29 September after the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) cut its benchmark interest rate by more than economists’ forecast. Its seven-day relative strength index climbed above 70 on Tuesday. Some investors see a level above this reading as a signal to sell.

For more updates, join our experts at the daily live chat from 12pm to 1pm as they gauge the markets today. For live Sensex updates, <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Money/zUWcjTfKB0FKKtssdbYQ9O/Live-Sensex-Nifty-snap-sixday-rally.html" target="_blank">click here</a>.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Amitabh Bachchan &#124; Today’s generation is a league apart from ours</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/news/amitabh-bachchan-todays-generation-is-a-league-apart-from-ours/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2015 07:03:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=108</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>New Delhi: </b>In a career spanning four-and-a-half decades, actor Amitabh Bachchan has seen the best and worst of stardom. A 15-year undisputed reign at the box office was followed by a sabbatical and some confused film choices, before he made a comeback in the new millennium having reinvented himself. This year, his 46th in the industry, he continued to warm hearts with his turn as the hypochondriac father in Shoojit Sircar’s <i>Piku</i>. His tryst with television continues as well—he will soon appear on Star Plus with <i>Aaj Ki Raat Hai Zindagi</i>. In an email interview, the internationally-acclaimed actor, India’s most popular television host and the face of numerous brands spoke about his life and his work just before he turns 73 on 11 October. Edited excerpts:

<b>You have a new television show called <i>Aaj Ki Raat Hai Zindagi </i>coming up on Star Plus. How is it to collaborate with the channel yet again? What is the show about? </b>

Yes, <i>Aaj ki Raat Hai Zindagi </i>is a new venture on Star Plus, and it’s good to be back with them after a while, albeit temporarily for I am still contracted with Sony for <i>Kaun Banega Crorepati </i>and have to complete that. Life is beautiful despite many obstacles that we face, and this is what the essence of the show is.

<b>It was reported that you’re personally looking into every aspect of the show—from creative to content. How is the preparation going?</b>

It’s always a joy to be involved in different aspects of a creative project that one is committed to, and this one is no less. From music to the structure of presentation and some additional ideas, it’s always good to share things with the team. If they are approved, fine. If not, you just follow what the team wants.

<b><i>Piku </i>was loved universally and is one of the most acclaimed films this year. What do you think worked most for it?</b>

I think it connected with every home and family. It was a slice of life from almost every individual’s daily routine. The writing was brilliant and the “not to fuss” vibe about its presentation, by Shoojit Sarkar, the director, was what made it work, I guess. There was no story, just events and chatter over the course of a few days in the life of Baba Bhaskor Bannerji and Piku, his daughter.

<b>Be it <i>Piku</i>, <i>Shamitabh </i>or the upcoming <i>Wazir</i>, what do you look for when you sign a film today? Over the years, has the criterion changed in any way?</b>

I do not look for anything. I just look for another job. And I am grateful that I get one.

<b>When you invest time and effort into pre-release marketing and promotion today, do you get reminded of the time when films would be released without these imperatives? Does it ever exhaust you?</b>

Times have changed and one has to change with time. Marketing has become an essential tool to strengthen the commercial prospects of any film. When you have just one weekend to recover your investment, you or those who are involved with the film need to promote and put the product out there in the most effective way possible. It is exhausting, but you have to feel the exhaustion of the investor, too.

<b>You’re a hugely popular brand ambassador and fans and audiences are likely to take seriously anything you choose to endorse. Is that a consideration when you choose your brands? </b>

I am not a hugely popular brand ambassador or anywhere near such an accolade. I just do what is asked of me. Some of it works, some does not.

<b>How do you make time for your blog and social media presence regularly? </b>

If you find time, time shall have time for you.

<b>Given your hectic work schedule, what do you look forward to the most at the end of a long day or week?</b>

Sleep.

<b>Do you get time to see new films? Which have been your favourite films and performances this year so far?</b>

Yes, I do. And a lot of interesting films are being made these days. I marvel at the makers and those who perform in them. I am most impressed and in awe of the talent that connects with our audiences today. It would be very difficult and unfair to pick an individual choice, but suffice to say that today’s generation is a league apart from ours. That is a compliment to them and a challenge to us.

<b>Is there something you’re most grateful for this year?</b>

Yes, of course. That I still breathe.

<b>Is there something in particular that you’ve learnt this past year? Do you have any regrets?</b>

There are no regrets at all. In fact, every nano-second is a lesson on life and the world. The more one exists, the greater is the capacity to gather more knowledge.

<b>Any wishes for the coming year?</b>

Yes. Dear Lord, protect and save me from the perils of self expression.]]></content:encoded>

		<wp:post_id>154</wp:post_id>

	<item>
		<title>Sign Up Requirements</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/sign-up-requirements/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 10:26:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=219</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Documents required to become a Paytm Seller

&nbsp;

·   PAN Card

o    PAN should be in the name of your business (except in case of sole proprietorship).

o    PAN image should be attested (signed and stamped) by authorized signatory of business.

·   Cancelled cheque for bank account verification

o    cheque should be in the name of registered business address

o    If the business name is not present, company stamp should be printed on cancelled cheque, or self declaration should be attached on company letter head along with the cheque.

·   VAT/TIN

o    In case of non-availability of a valid VAT/TIN, a self-declaration form on the company letter head along with signature and stamp has to be submitted

o    VAT/TIN image should be attested (signed and stamped) by the authorized signatory of the business.

·   Address Proof

o    Address proof of registered business address.

o    Address Proof Image should be attested (signed and stamped) by authorized signatory of business

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;">SignUp Now</p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Return Policies</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/return-policies/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:33:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=292</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[For simplicity, at Paytm we classify all the return cases either as <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/rto-process-policies/">DTO or as RTO</a>. The generic process and policies relating to retuns process can be found below.

<strong><u>Return Process Flow Chart-1</u></strong>

Item Delivered &gt; Return Request &gt; Request Approved &gt; E-mail notification to merchant &gt; Courier Assigned &gt; Return Picked &gt; Merchant receives return

The above process has certain exceptions (covered in flow chart-2), which may be related to the following cases:-
<ol>
	<li>For certain low valued products, Paytm refunds the customer without arranging a pickup. In such cases seller doesn’t bear any costs.</li>
	<li>At time our courier partner might not be available for pickup or the area might not be within serviceable limits. In such cases, the customer self ships the return. Paytm credits the courier charges to customer and debits the merchant.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Flow Chart-2</strong>

<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-345" src="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png" alt="Untitled" width="844" height="1046" /></a>

&nbsp;

<em>NSS: Non Shippable Service: Pincodes which Paytm LMD  doesn’t cover</em>
<em>NSS &gt;= 400 : Product price is more than 400 &amp; is to be picked from NSS area</em>
<em>SS: Shippable Service: Pincodes covered under Paytm LMD</em>
<em>SS &lt; 100 : Product value is less than 100 &amp; is to be picked from SS area</em>

The above process is applicable for sellers availing the Last Mile Delivery (LMD) service offered by Paytm where Paytm takes care of all the logistic related needs (details can be found <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/lmd-vs-nlmd/">here</a>). Seller panel related details for these merchants can be found here. Sellers not availing Last Mile Delivery service have to organize the return pickup on their own. Seller panel related details for these merchants can be found here.

<strong><u>Return Process Stages Explained</u></strong>

The following states would be visible to the Seller via the Returns tab on the Seller Panel:-

<u>Return Requested
</u>The customer wants the product to be returned. So a return request is sent through Paytm.
<u>
Return Approved
</u>The returns are approved after a preliminary investigation by Paytm.
<u>Return Pending
</u>When a product is returned in the shipped state, it goes to the Return Pending State.

<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Return Picked</span>
The item is picked from the customer by the delivery partner. <u></u>

<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Returned</span>
The item is delivered to the merchant. <u></u>

Average Time spent on States (Return)

<u> </u>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="313"><strong>State</strong></td>
<td width="311"><strong>Time ( hours)</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="313">1.      Return Requested</td>
<td width="311">32.25</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="313">2.      Return Approved</td>
<td width="311">77.75</td>

(excluding Return Rejected)</td>

</table>
<strong><u> </u></strong>

<strong><u>Policies &amp; Timelines</u></strong>

Depending on the category a product belongs to, the return reasons and applicable return policies available with the customer can be found <a href="https://drive.google.com/a/paytm.com/file/d/0BxRCcYeSLizFV1hGdkVVOHlqRUU/view?usp=sharing">here.</a>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="125">Product Category</td>
<td width="125">Return Reasons</td>
<td width="125">Order cancellable</td>
<td width="125">Return policy text</td>
<td width="125">Return in Days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="125"></td>
<td width="125"></td>
<td width="125"></td>
<td width="125"></td>
<td width="125"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;

<strong><u>Legal Clauses related to returns</u></strong>
<ul>
	<li>Non delivery/return of the Product due to fault of the Seller Where the Product has not been delivered/ has been returned due to any reason/fault attributable to Seller, then Paytm shall refund to the Buyer the Selling Price paid by the Buyer to purchase the Product and Seller shall be liable to pay Paytm and Paytm shall be entitled to recover from Seller - Paytm Marketing Fee, Courier Charges, Payment Collection Fees, Fulfillment Charges (if applicable) and Seller Proceeds (where Paytm has remitted the Seller Proceeds to the Seller)</li>
	<li>Non delivery/return of the Product due to any other reason Where the Product has not been delivered/ has been returned due to any reason which is not attributable to the Seller, then Paytm shall refund to the Buyer, the Selling Price paid by the Buyer to purchase the Product and shall cause the Product to be returned to the Seller. Upon confirmation of return of Product back to Seller in appropriate condition, Paytm is entitled to recover any proceeds paid to Seller for that Product.</li>
	<li>Seller hereby agree to accept all Products (cash on delivery or non-cash on delivery), which are refused/not accepted by the Buyer at the time of delivery.</li>
	<li>The Seller undertakes to bear all logistics cost with respect to return/reverse orders and also acknowledges that Reverse Logistics Cost as stated in Commercial Rate Segment</li>
	<li>Seller undertakes to accept all the return shipments irrespective of condition of the shipment and any dispute with respect to the condition of the shipment shall be settled by the Parties only after acceptance of the shipment by Seller. If the shipment is not accepted by Seller, no dispute related to returns shall be entertained by Paytm.</li>
	<li>Seller undertakes to provide its signature along with its stamp with receiver customer’s  name /contact number on all return shipments without which courier will not handover any shipment .In absence of such evidence on return shipments, no return shipment query will be entertained.</li>
	<li>Seller undertakes to put return shipment queries with merchant helpdesk only in form of tickets within 72 hours of receiving of shipments failing which such queries of Seller shall not be considered by Paytm. In case of receipt of damaged product, Seller undertakes to send 360 deg photos within 72 hours of receiving such product.</li>
	<li>Cancellation, refund and replacement</li>
	<li>Further in case of order cancellation, refund, replacement of product due to any reason as mentioned in agreement or below mentioned table, Seller shall be liable to pay charges as per the below mentioned table:</li>
</ul>
<table width="617">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="50">Sr. No.</td>
<td width="200">Particulars</td>
<td width="113">Marketing Fees</td>
<td width="130">Payment Collection Charges</td>
<td width="124">Customer Retention Charges</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50">1</td>
<td width="200">Damaged/ Defective/ Wrong SKU shipment</td>
<td width="113">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="130">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="124">10% of Selling Price</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50">2</td>
<td width="200">Refund/ Replacement in case of wrong size, color issues</td>
<td width="113">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="130">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="124">NA</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50">3</td>
<td width="200">Post Shipment return upto a period of 30 days from delivery, because of product quality issue</td>
<td width="113">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="130">To be borne by Seller</td>
<td width="124">10% of Selling Price</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;

Fuerhwe details relating to legal clauses can be found here (link to full merchant agreement)

<strong><u>Return Logistics Cost</u></strong>
<ul>
	<li>Paytm charges Rs. 63 per 500 gm for return logistics from sellers availing the Last Mile Delivery service in case it’s an air delivery</li>
	<li>Rs 20 / Kg would be charged for surface delivery. . However minimum chargeable weight for surface deliveries will be 5 KG. Service tax would be extra.</li>
</ul>
<strong><u>Returns processing via Panel</u></strong>

Seller panel related training for processing returns can be found here (To be done by Paromita)

<strong><u>Return Dispute Resolution</u></strong>

Sellers enjoy all the rights to raise a dispute relating to returns. Paytm will decide such cases after investigation. For raising a dispute relating to returns Seller should mark a mail to

Mark a mail to <a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</a> within 72 hours of receiving the return.

Paytm has recently introduced its state of the art Return Processing Centers (RPCs) across the country. You can read more about RPCs<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/rpc/"> here</a>.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Payouts</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/payouts/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:36:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=294</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm is proud to offers its sellers the fastest payment cycle in the marketplace and for the ease of sellers’ we have ensured that  payments are made twice or thrice in a week for the sales done by them. The seller receives Payment email from Paytm once the dispatched order shows 'Delivered' status in the system.The PDF invoices (after deducting sum of marketplace commission+ Payment gateway + Logistics (LMD partner) + penalty if any) along with the orders/payouts is e-mailed to the sellers and the funds are transferred in seller's bank account. However, the banks normally  take 2-3 days for these funds to reflect in seller's account.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Payout cycle thrice in a week (M, W, F) on the basis of delivered orders on system. Payment against this payout will reflect in merchant accounts within 7days after delivery of product.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For example order delivered till Sunday payout will be done for these orders in Monday cycle and order delivered between Monday to Tuesday payout will be done for these orders in Wednesday cycle and order delivered betweenWednesday to Thursday payout will be done for these orders in Friday cycle.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A seller has complete access and can view all detailed orders and earnings for products in the </span><b>Payment</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> tab of </span><b>Seller Panel</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The Payment tab lists details pertaining to Payment Dashboard, All payments, Unpaid Orders and All Order details.</span></p>

<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Payment Dashboard</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> :The sellers will be able to make use of Payment Dashboard very soon as it is  expected to go live very  soon with a feature  where sellers would be able to view the date wise break up of their payments.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>All Payments</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: This tab gives an insight to all your earnings, deductions or </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">penalties.  You can view the payment break up by clicking on 'View Payment Details' in this tab. By clicking on 'View Orders' the seller can check for any deductions on his orders if any and enables you to download Order CSV file to check for orders. </span></li>
</ol>
<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Unpaid Orders</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: This tab has a detailed list of all the unpaid orders and allows you to download </span><b>Order CSV </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">file . Sellers can easily access and view logistic and marketplace fee here and any deductions that he would have to bear for certain product refunds.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>All Orders</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">:The last tab in Payments is </span><b>All Orders</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> where we can view all the orders payout with their complete status.</span></li>
</ol>
You may like to read more about the following topics:-

<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/various-fee/">Various Fee</a>

<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/commissions-2/">Commissions</a>

<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/modes-of-payments/">Modes of Payment</a>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You are always welcome to ask a question or to get a solution of your query on Payments. We are alway reachable at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><b>merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</b></a><b>.</b></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Legal Policies</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/legal-policies/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:44:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=296</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Legal Policies</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"> OBLIGATIONS OF THE SELLER</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller shall maintain records of all the Products purchased by the Buyers through the Platform, all returns, refunds, etc., as may be required for audit and regulatory purposes and for the Platform’s customer service purposes.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         During the Term, Seller shall appoint a representative, who shall be Paytm’s point of contact for any and all matters related to this Agreement, including all sales and delivery related matters.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                       III.         Seller shall be solely responsible and liable for any complaints and queries of Buyers with respect to the Products, delayed delivery or non-delivery of the Products purchased or any complaints with respect to the quality or quantity of the Products delivered.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller shall be solely responsible for making any representations or warranties with respect to the quality of the Product to the Buyer, including all relevant Product warranties.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller shall, at all times, comply with all applicable laws including without limitation compliance with laws relating to sales tax, VAT etc.</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">OBLIGATIONS OF THE SELLER ON MALPRACTICE</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller confirms and understands that selling and delivering wrong, fake, duplicate, spurious, counterfeit, damaged, defective, refurbished or previously owned Products through the Platform will cause great prejudice and harm to the reputation and goodwill of Paytm and may also cause harm and prejudice to the Buyers. Seller acknowledges and warrants that Seller shall not sell any Product which may cause prejudice or harm to the reputation and goodwill of Paytm. Paytm reserves the right to impose and deduct from the outstanding payments of the Seller without prior consent of the Seller or recover damages from the Seller if the Seller is found to be involved in any malpractice. </span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller undertakes and agrees that product Catalogue listing details in Paytm portal shall be true, correct, and duly authorized and shall not be misleading, fraudulent, false, unauthorized, illegal and shall not contain any misrepresentation of facts to induce users for ordering for Sellers products listed on Paytm portal. If the Seller is found to be involved in any such misrepresentation or illegal activity, the Seller acknowledges that Paytm reserves its right to terminate this Agreement immediately and claim damages apart from making itself liable for criminal prosecution.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                        III.         Seller undertakes and agrees to dispatch and deliver only that/those products which were ordered by the User on Portal and not to dispatch empty box or any other product of lesser value. If Seller is found to be involved dispatching or delivering empty box or any other product of lesser value to the user thereby resulting in loss of reputation or goodwill, the same shall be regarded as gross violation of the terms and conditions of the Agreement and Seller acknowledges that Paytm reserves its right to take actions.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller undertakes and agrees he shall not collude with a User/s for the purpose of consumption of cashback amount through false and fraudulent transaction or represent/pose as User in order to consume the cashback offer of Paytm. Seller further acknowledges he shall not place orders with his own or relative’s account for earning cash back offers. If Seller is found to involved in such activity, the same shall amount to malpractice under this Agreement and the Seller acknowledges that Paytm reserves its right to take actions.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller undertakes and confirms that it deals only in original, legitimate and genuine Products which are either self-manufactured and/or procured from legitimate channels and in compliance with all the legal requirements. Seller further undertakes that it shall not sell fake/spurious/non authentic products on the Platform. For the purpose of this Agreement, fake/spurious/non authentic products shall means and include the following:-</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">a)     If the product received by the User is different from that shown/displayed in the image uploaded on Paytm’s site by the Seller</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">b)     If the Seller is not authorized to sell a product which may either be branded /non branded)</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">c)      If a Seller commits a warranty for a product on Paytm website which it is not authorized to do</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">d)     If the Seller interchanges warranties between seller and brand</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">e)     If the Seller tampers with Maximum Retail Price (MRP) label of the product, uses outdated packages, makes false representation as to price, date and quality and tampers with any packaging as mandated by Legal Metrology Act and all other applicable laws.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Seller is found to be selling fake/spurious/non authentic products, the same shall amount to gross      violation under this agreement and the Seller acknowledges that Paytm reserves its right to take actions.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller undertakes and confirms that while listing the inventory of the product, the Seller has physical possession and owns such quantity of product as listed on Paytm and further undertakes to fulfill the orders placed by the user promptly.  In the event of delay in shipment/delivery of products or Seller cancellation of orders due to non-availability of products, the Seller acknowledges that Paytm reserves its right to take actions</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                       VII.         Seller acknowledges that Paytm has the right to cap the maximum quantity of product that the Seller may list in Paytm website in order to control the maximum number of order Seller can receive and deliver the orders on time.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">                      VIII.         Seller confirms Seller shall not create multiple accounts with Paytm which may lead to misrepresentation of identity of the account holders of those accounts. Seller may also not create multiple IDs under the category of user wherein the identities of those user accounts do not represent the Seller. Seller is in gross violation of the Agreement if he holds multiple user or Seller accounts.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">TRANSFER OF OWNERSHIP OF PRODUCT, LOGISTICS AND CONSUMER RIGHTS</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller agrees that Paytm’s role is limited to managing the Platform for the display of the Products and other incidental services to facilitate the transactions between Seller and the Buyers. Accordingly, Paytm is merely an intermediary and the Platform is only a platform where the Seller may offer its Products for sale. The contract for sale of any of the Products shall be a strictly bipartite contract between Seller and the Buyer. At no time shall Paytm have any obligations or liabilities in respect of such contract nor shall Paytm hold any rights, title or interest in the Products. Paytm shall not be responsible for any unsatisfactory or delayed performance of the Seller including delays as a result of the Products being out of stock.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The ownership in the Products purchased will be transferred to the Buyer after successful delivery of the same at the destination provided by the Buyer, until which the ownership in the Products shall vest with the Seller alone. As a large market place, Paytm will extend its services to Sellers by giving mandates to logistic partners for facilitating the smooth functioning of the transaction between Seller and the Buyer. Any damage in transit on account of inadequate/unsuitable packaging will be to the account of the Seller.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                       III.         Seller hereby agrees to accept all sales return (cash on delivery or non-cash on delivery), which are refused/not accepted by the Buyer at the time of delivery.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller will offer standard manufacturers or seller’s warranty actually associated with the Products. However, the Parties agree that repair, replacement or 100% (one hundred percent) refund of money will be given to the Buyer against manufacturing defect or damage. Seller shall issue a suitable, duly stamped, manufacturer’s warranty card to the Buyer with the Product at the time of dispatch of the Product, if applicable. The Parties also agree and acknowledge that the primary and sole responsibility for redressal of the Buyer’s complaints will rest solely with Seller at all times</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Parties hereby represent and warrant to each other as under:</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Parties have all requisite power and authority to execute the Agreement, deliver and perform their obligations under this Agreement and have been fully authorized by all requisite corporate actions to do so; and</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The execution and performance of this Agreement by either Party does not and will not violate any provision of any existing agreement, law, rule, regulation, any order or judicial pronouncement.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                       III.         The Seller undertakes that, at all times during the Term of this Agreement, it will:</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">a)     abide by the terms and conditions of the Agreement, the Paytm Policies and the other Platform policies, as may be applicable to the Seller;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">b)     not offer for sale/sell/deliver any Banned Products or refurbished Products on the Platform;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">c)      deliver the Products to the Buyers in a timely manner consistent with the terms of this Agreement; and</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">d)     deliver the Products in accordance with all applicable laws, rules, regulations, governmental orders, etc., and applicable codes of practice, now or hereafter in effect, relating to the Seller’s performance under this Agreement.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller represents that the Seller is competent to contract and is not disqualified from contracting under any law in India.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller has and shall maintain all licenses and registrations required for selling the Products online or otherwise during the Term.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller agrees, represents and warrants that the Seller shall not describe himself/itself as an agent or representative of Paytm or make any representations to any Buyer or any third party or give any warranties which are of such a nature that Paytm may be required to undertake, or be liable for, whether directly or indirectly.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                      VII.         The Seller agrees, represents and warrants that the Seller shall not, during the Term, offer the Products listed on the Platform, to any other website or through any other platform, at a price which is less than the Selling Price, as listed on the Platform.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">                     VIII.         Seller agrees, represents and warrants that, the Seller shall not, at any time during the Term, transact with any Buyer directly.The Seller agrees to attend to, and resolve, the Buyers queries with regard to the delivery of the Products and the quantity and quality of the Products within 1 (one) day from the date of receipt of such queries.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller hereby represents and warrants to Paytm that there are no restrictions, hindrances or encumbrances of any nature which, in any manner, restrict the performance of the obligations by the Seller under this Agreement.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller shall be responsible for payment of the Seller’s own taxes and any taxes/levies/cess applicable on the Products sold through the Platform, and shall indemnify and hold harmless, Paytm, from any liability in this regard.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Seller hereby declares and confirms that it deals only in original, legitimate and genuine Products which are either self-manufactured and/or procured from legitimate channels and in compliance with all the legal requirements. The Seller further declares that it shall not violate the intellectual property rights of any third party and for any breach or violation of such intellectual property rights, it shall be solely responsible.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                      XII.         The content of the Products, the text descriptions, graphics or pictures regarding the Product being uploaded on the Platform and the Product packaging, shall not be obscene, libelous, defamatory or scandalous or which is capable of hurting the religious sentiments of any segment of the population or constitute an infringement of any intellectual property rights of any person or entity.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">                     XIII.         Seller agrees, acknowledge and understand that:</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">a)     Seller is using the Platform provided and owned by Paytm;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">b)     The permission granted by Paytm to use the Platform as an online market place is on a non-exclusive basis;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">c)      Paytm reserves the right to deny access to, or revoke, such permission to use the Seller Panel and/or Platform at any time;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">d)     Paytm shall have the right to remove the listing of any Product being offered for sale by Seller;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">e)     Paytm shall have the right to offer discounts, run promotion campaigns on the Selling Price to the Buyers from Paytm’s Marketing Fee. Seller shall not object to the provision of such discounts given by Paytm;</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">f)       Any and all data derived as a result of this Agreement will be owned by Paytm and Seller shall have the right to utilize such data for the duration of the Term of this Agreement to fulfill Seller’s obligations hereunder; and</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">g)     For the duration of the Term, the Platform shall be maintained by Paytm. The ownership of the Platform shall vest with Paytm and Paytm shall make its best efforts to deal with any technical issues affecting the Platform (such as, for instance, the Platform becoming inoperative. Paytm does not warrant that the Seller will be able to use the Platform and offer for sale the Seller’s Products at all times or locations on the Platform or that the Platform and the services provided through the Platform will be uninterrupted or error-free or that the defects will be corrected by Paytm.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">h)     Except as agreed to by the Parties, the data of Buyers will be the exclusive property of Paytm, and Seller will not use the same for Seller’s own purpose or distribute such data in any form or means except for the purpose of this Agreement and shall keep it confidential at all times.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">i)       In the event of any breach or delay in the fulfillment of Seller’s obligations by Seller, due to any reason, Paytm shall not be held liable/responsible. Paytm shall not be liable for the sale of the Products by Seller through the Platform or any loss incurred by Seller or the Buyer therefrom.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">j)       The Seller represents that the Seller shall not, at any time, use any intellectual property of Paytm in any manner without the prior written consent of Paytm. The Seller also represents that the Seller shall not purchase any Paytm metatags on the Internet without the prior written consent of Paytm.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">k)      Seller agree that Seller will abide by the terms and conditions of this Agreement and Paytm Policies, including any amendments thereto made by Paytm from time to time which may be made without notice to Seller.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">l)       The Seller represents and warrants that if Seller is found indulging in providing of false or misleading information or provision of defective or counterfeit Products, then Paytm may initiate civil and/or criminal proceedings against the Seller and Paytm may, at its sole discretion, suspend, block, restrict, or cancel the Seller’s registration on the Platform and /or disqualify / bar the Seller from selling the Products on the Platform.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;"> INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Both Parties agree that the brands/logos, trademarks, etc., belonging to each Party are the exclusive property of the respective Party and cannot in any circumstances be used, or copied, or altered in any manner which is identical/ similar the brands/logos/trademarks of the other Party without being specifically authorized in writing by that other Party. Seller recognizes and confirms that Paytm has the exclusive right to supervise, allow and reject the contents of the Platform. Paytm shall not be liable for contents and images shared, uploaded or displayed on the Platform by the Seller regarding the Seller’s Products and all consequent liability will be borne by the Seller only.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller hereby grants to Paytm the right to display/delist the Products (as updated or to be updated by Seller on the Seller Panel at any/all times) along with the related logo and/or trademark and/or brand name, etc., of the Products for marketing/selling through the Platform.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">                       III.         Seller hereby authorize Paytm to use and include Seller’s trademarks (as may be provided by Seller from time to time) and Seller’s corporate name on the Platform and in any directory or promotional material produced in connection with the promotion of the Platform or the Products offered by Seller on the Platform.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         Seller acknowledges that Paytm is merely an intermediary with respect to the Products listed on the Platform. However, on receiving written notification of any alleged infringement of third party intellectual property rights due to display or sale of any Products/third party trademark or copyrighted matter on the Platform (including availability or sale of counterfeit goods on the Platform), Paytm may, at its own discretion, remove / delist the allegedly infringing Products / content from the Platform, with or without prior notice to Seller.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">ANTI BRIBERY AND ANTI CORRUPTION POLICY</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         The Parties agree to conduct all their dealings in a very ethical manner and with the highest business standards. The Seller agrees to comply with Anti-Bribery and Anti-Corruption Policy and adopt appropriate processes to prevent offering any illegal gratification in the form of bribes or gifts either in cash or in kind in the course of all dealings with Paytm or any other third parties for the purpose of this Agreement. Any instances of such violations will be viewed in a serious manner and Paytm reserves the right to take all appropriate actions or remedies as may be required under the circumstances. The Seller will provide all possible assistance to Paytm in order to investigate any possible instances of unethical behavior or business conduct violations by an employee or hired person of the Seller.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">.   GENERAL TERMS</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         DISPUTE RESOLUTION, GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION: If any dispute arises between the Parties hereto during the subsistence of this Agreement or thereafter, in connection with, or arising out of, this Agreement, the dispute shall be referred to arbitration under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (Indian) to be adjudicated by a sole arbitrator to be appointed by Paytm. Arbitration shall be held at New Delhi, India. The proceedings of arbitration shall be in the English language. The arbitrator’s award shall be final and binding on the Parties. The Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. The courts of New Delhi, India, shall have exclusive jurisdiction in connection with this Agreement.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         CONFIDENTIALITY: The parties shall not at any time divulge, or allow to be divulged to any person, any Confidential Information unless the said information comes in public domain without breach by either Party however, no party shall be precluded from disclosing any information to the extent required in the legal proceedings. Confidential information would include but not be limited to Buyer details, market information, all work Products and documents related thereto, the contents of the Platform or any other information which is treated as confidential by Paytm, and any other information, whether oral or in writing, received or to be received by Seller which is agreed to be treated under the same terms, whether expressly or by implication. The obligations under this Clause shall survive the termination of this Agreement</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">     III.         FORCE MAJEURE: No Party shall be liable for failure to perform its obligations due to Force Majeure.</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         NOTICES: to be served by email or post to the addresses as stated above.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         ASSIGNMENT: Parties shall not have the right to assign this Agreement except assigned to affiliates.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">         MODIFICATION: Shall be effective or binding if agreed in writing by authorized representatives.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">EXCLUSIVITY: Seller agrees that Product sold by them will be launched exclusively at Paytm Platform and shall exclusively available at Paytm Platform for a period of 3 months from launch of Seller’s product. Upon expiry of the period of exclusivity, both the parties may at their sole discretion mutually agree on extension of such exclusivity period. However, if Seller enters into an agreement with other website or platform upon expiry of the exclusivity period, Seller will inform Paytm 20 (twenty) days in advance before entering into any such arrangement.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">RESTRICTED CATEGORIES:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">(i) Adult goods and services which includes pornography and other sexually suggestive materials (including literature, imagery and other media); escort or prostitution services; (ii) Alcohol which includes Alcohol or alcoholic beverages such as beer, liquor, wine, or champagne; Body parts which includes organs or other body parts; (iv) Bulk marketing tools which includes email lists, software, or other products enabling unsolicited email messages (Spam); (v) Cable descramblers and black boxes which includes devices intended to obtain cable and satellite signals for free; (vi) Child pornography which includes pornographic materials involving minors; (vii) Copyright unlocking devices which includes Mod chips or other devices designed to circumvent copyright protection; (viii) Copyrighted media, which includes unauthorized copies of books, music, movies, and other licensed or protected materials; (ix) Copyrighted software, which includes unauthorized copies of software, video games and other licensed or protected materials, including OEM or bundled software; (x) Counterfeit and unauthorized goods which includes replicas or imitations of designer goods; items without a celebrity endorsement that would normally require such an association; fake autographs, counterfeit stamps, and other potentially unauthorized goods; (xi) Drugs and drug paraphernalia which includes illegal drugs and drug accessories, including herbal drugs like salvia and magic mushrooms; (xii) Drug test circumvention aids which includes drug cleansing shakes, urine test additives, and related items; (xiii) Endangered species, which includes plants, animals or other organisms (including product derivatives) in danger of extinction; (xiv) Gaming/gambling which includes lottery tickets, sports bets, memberships/ enrolment in online gambling sites, and related content;</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Government IDs or documents which includes fake IDs, passports, diplomas, and noble titles; (xv) Hacking and cracking materials which includes manuals, how-to guides, information, or equipment enabling illegal access to software, servers, websites, or other protected property; (xvi) Illegal goods, which includes materials, products, or information promoting illegal goods or enabling illegal acts; (xvii) Miracle cures which includes unsubstantiated cures, remedies or other items marketed as quick health fixes; (xviii) Offensive goods, which includes literature, products or other materials that: a) Defame or slander any person or groups of people based on race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, sex, or other factors b) Encourage or incite violent acts c) Promote intolerance or hatred;</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">(xix) Offensive goods, crime that includes crime scene photos or items, such as personal belongings, associated with criminals; (xxi) Prescription drugs or herbal drugs or any kind of online pharmacies which includes drugs or other products requiring a prescription by a licensed medical practitioner; (xxii) Pyrotechnic devices and hazardous materials which includes fireworks and related goods; toxic, flammable, and radioactive materials and substances; (xxiii) Regulated goods which includes air bags; batteries containing mercury; Freon or similar substances/refrigerants; chemical/industrial solvents; government uniforms; car titles; license plates; police badges and law enforcement equipment; lock-picking devices; pesticides; postage meters; recalled items; slot machines; surveillance equipment; goods regulated by government or other agency specifications; (xxiv) Securities, which includes stocks, bonds, or related financial products; (xxv)Tobacco and cigarettes which includes cigarettes, cigars, chewing tobacco, and related products; (xxvi) Traffic devices, which includes radar detectors/hammers, license plate covers, traffic signal changers, and related products; (xxvii) Weapons which includes firearms, ammunition, knives, brass knuckles, gun parts, and other armaments; (xxix) Wholesale currency, which includes discounted currencies or currency, exchanges; (xxx) Live animals; (xxxi) Multi Level marketing collection fees; (xxxii) Matrix sites or sites using a matrix scheme approach; (xxxiii) Work-at-home information; (xxxiv) Drop-shipped merchandise; (xxxv) Collecting and effecting / remitting payments directly /indirectly outside India in any form towards overseas foreign exchange trading through electronic/internet trading portals; and (xxxvi) Any product or service, which is not in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations whether federal, state, local or international including the all laws of India</span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Seller Ratings</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/seller-ratings/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:45:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=298</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Boost online sales with perfect ratings!</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The power of seller ratings on any marketplace is enormous, as your customers trust online reviews and consider the ratings/reviews as personal recommendations. You must target for good ratings as it helps you in following ways:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">High ratings increase your sales &amp; identify you as a trusted seller</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Helps give more visibility to your product</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">High rating means people trust you and prefer to buy from you</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">The seller ratings on Paytm marketplace are a great way to speak for your performance, ranking and the services you give for your products. In today's eCommerce world, we cannot ignore the vast influence of internet shoppers as our customers refer and trust seller ratings before placing an order. Currently,  on Paytm a customer can rate you on three aspects :-</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product as described</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product Packaging and Handling</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Timely Delivery</span></li>
</ol>
<b>Ways to improve rating-</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product description- Give true and genuine description of the product.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Packaging and Handling- Adhere to Paytm packaging guidelines. Ensure to pack and ship every order with utmost care to avoid any damage or breakage while handling. You can learn more about detailed </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/#/trainingCentre"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm’s packaging guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for each category on Seller Panel.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Timely delivery- Make sure to deliver an order on time.Check that </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">you are packing and getting orders ready for shipment within 24 hours - This will help boost your overall average ratings. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quality-You must ensure shipping best quality products to ensure reduced returns from customers.  To achieve this, use great quality images, give accurate product description and ship the exact product that you have displayed on the marketplace. </span></li>
</ul>
<b>Things to avoid</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not sell fake </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not give false description of products</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not ship wrong product other than what is shown to the buyer on the Paytm website Make sure you do not ship used, faulty and re-furbished products</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not give false description in Product’s attributes like size and colour</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not forget to send freebies</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">and other offers that you promised with the main product</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case you require any help/advice relating to rating, feel free to mail us at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">   </span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Penalties</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/penalties/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:47:57 +0000</pubDate>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span data-sheets-value="[null,2,&quot;Merchant Fraud and Common Mistakes to Avoid&quot;]" data-sheets-userformat="[null,null,513,[null,0],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0]"><a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/merchant-fraud-and-common-mistakes-to-avoid/">Merchant Fraud and Common Mistakes to Avoid</a></span>

<span data-sheets-value="[null,2,&quot;Penalties&quot;]" data-sheets-userformat="[null,null,513,[null,0],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0]"><a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/merchant-penalties/">Merchant Penalties</a></span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Merchant Fraud and  Common Mistakes to Avoid</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/merchant-fraud-and-common-mistakes-to-avoid/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 12:29:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=325</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>MERCHANT FRAUD,  MALPRACTICE &amp; COMMON</b><b> MISTAKES TO AVOID </b>

<b>What is a fraud? (In the context of E-commerce business)</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Fraud – at Paytm – is considered to be a deliberate action of deceiving Paytm or its partners to secure unfair or unlawful gain which may hamper customer experience directly or indirectly as well as may cause damages (financial, Brand Image, False Representation, Loss of Business) to Paytm, its resources or its partners. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm promotes fair practice of conducting genuine transactions on its platform, and a fraudulent activity goes against this commitment.</span>

<b>Below are some of the cases which are classified under fraudulent malpractice under Merchant Fraud:</b>

<b>Collusion: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">This typically exist in the nature where the Merchant and / or buyer are not entering into a genuine &amp; valid transaction. Paytm may penalize and take severe actions on a merchant under this case. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To avoid this, a merchant</span><b> must not</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enter into a transaction(s) with the buyer where the nature of transaction is induced to cause damages or commit fraud</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enter or receive orders that indicate an unnatural and biased order velocity trend</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Impersonate a buyer to book invalid orders under natural, unbiased circumstances </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Receive orders from a suspicious, fake or not a genuine customer</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Work with any other party to receive fraudulent orders that indicate an ingenuine transaction and typically cause damages to Paytm.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Place orders for his own products, especially taking advantage of the offers and promotions meant for other genuine customers</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li><b><b>Shipping anything other than the product ordered:</b></b></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A seller is committed to deliver the exact same product that the customer has ordered. Falling short of this commitment is considered as a severe case of Fraud.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Hence merchant</span><b> should not: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ship a replica of the product ordered</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ship a used /refurbished product that may represent or look like the product ordered but is not in actual</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ship partial product or ship any object / product that does not (in look, feel or value) represent the same product </span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">If the count of your Empty box cases are more than 0.1% of the entire orders with Paytm, you are liable to pay heavy penalty and being barred from doing business on the Paytm platform.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A seller is responsible for the shipments leaving his facility, and must take necessary steps for monitoring the picking, packing and shipping of products in his workplace. Please note, that a seller is accountable for any mistake and malpractice of the personnel and workforce in his facility.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Below are some of the best practices which </span><b>must be</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> followed by a merchant:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always maintain a stock of authentic brand new products </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ensure that the image on the catalog is that of the same product</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep a CCTV camera to monitor shop floor and physical inspection of products helps improve the quality of fulfillment</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always employ a workforce comprising of sincerity and good work ethics</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Employing processes and checks to increase the accountability and quality will ensure such activities do not happen</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li><b><b>Product Price &amp; Stock Changes:</b></b></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<b>Correct representation of Product information helps Customers know exactly what they are spending their money on. One key aspects of product information is maintaining accurate and correct MRP, SP &amp; Quantity in Physical stock of the product.</b>

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller must not misrepresent MRP of the product or show false discounts to induce sales</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller must not sell above statutory MRP,  doing so invites a heavy penalty</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller must not provide Paytm with incorrect SKU information in the seller’s catalog including MRP, SP and quantities in physical stock</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">While indicating the inventory of the product, seller has the responsibility of physically owning the quantity and must fulfill the orders promptly, otherwise Paytm may penalize the seller for damages caused in case of delayed shipments and merchant cancellations</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller must not tamper with the original MRP sticker on the product</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Best Practices:</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always maintain physical stock of products that you show in the system</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always keep the correct MRP of each of the product in your stock at the time of creating a new product in the system or at the time of changing the MRP of the product</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep a periodic check of your stock and ensure that the quantity is correctly entered in the system</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always ship products with an MRP sticker or the MRP of the product mentioned on the packaging</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li><b><b>Selling Fakes:</b></b></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm is committed to provide genuine, brand new and quality products to its customers. As a seller you are expected to do the same.  </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Examples of such cases where a seller </span><b>must avoid:</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling Fakes, Duplicates or Replicas of Branded Products</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling a branded product which you are not authorized to do so</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling a product which is sub-par in quality than the quality it was originally manufactured by the authorized manufacturer</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling a different product of lesser value, quality or specifications as ordered by the customer and displayed on the seller’s product display page</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling used or refurbished products and passing them as new to the customer</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller committing to a warranty on a product which he is not authorized to provide</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">All of the above examples are of fraudulent malpractice a seller should never indulge in. </span>

<b>Best Practices:</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always ensure that the warranty you offer on the product is valid and correct</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always procure genuine, original and quality products</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are the owner of the brand and ready to sell– keep all original documents of the brand ownership and authorization</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are a brand authorized seller – then you must have a valid brand authorization letter</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always maintain a record of purchase of your stock</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are selling products that have an IMEI, Serial no. then ensure that you have necessary details of the same</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>A non-responsive merchant: </b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<b>As a seller you must always keep a track of orders being booked and ship them as early as possible for a pleasant customer experience. As a non – responsive merchant you are liable for penal action:</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you do not acknowledge orders on time ( typically taking more than 2 days)</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you frequently cancel the orders that you receive </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you do not login into the Paytm Seller panel frequently to check and process your orders</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you do not respond to Paytm reminders (email or phone) for order processing</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Note:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Paytm reserves the right to impose, deduct from the outstanding payments of the seller or recover penalty without prior consent of the seller if the seller is found to be involved in any of the above mentioned </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Malpractices or Fraudulent activities</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span>

<b>Important: </b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A merchant must not misrepresent his / her identity to Paytm or create multiple accounts, which is immediately termed as having an intention to commit fraud </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A merchant must not create multiple customer ID’s wherein the identities of those customer accounts do not represent the merchant – doing so is immediately considered as intention of committing fraud</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Merchant penalties</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/merchant-penalties/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 12:42:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=338</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Penal action that Paytm is authorized to take in case a Seller is found to be committing fraud or using unfair means to gain proceeds from Paytm.</span>

&nbsp;
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><b>Event – Cases of Malpractice</b></td>
<td><b>Action taken by Paytm</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">MB Collusion</span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty will be applied as = [GMV + CB]*3</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Possible Delisting from Paytm Platform</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Empty Box </span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = GMV of valid empty box cases</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty recovery = 3*(GMV+CB) of EB cases</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Permanent Delisting - if total such cases exceed 0.1% of total lifetime orders</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selling Fakes</span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = 3* [GMV of all orders with fake products]</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Permanent Delisting from Paytm platform</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">MRP mismatch issue</span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = [(GMV of orders with bad MRP) * (no. of occurrence of the MRP issue)]</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">(if it’s the second such occurrence – penalty will be [2*GMV of order with bad MRP]</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">No response </span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = [5% of cancelled order value]</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pre SLA merchant cancellation</span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = [PG Fee + 50% Marketplace fee]</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Post SLA merchant cancellation</span></td>
<td>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Penalty = [PG Fee + 100% Marketplace fee]</span></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
