	<item>
		<title>RPC</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/rpc/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 05:32:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=360</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2>1.1   What is RPC?</h2>
As per the new Paytm policy, items that are returned by the customer will be sent to Paytm’s Returns Processing Center (RPC).

A Returns Processing Center is a physical hub where the merchandise returned by the customer is brought for quality check before it is dispatched further to the merchant.

The products will be quality checked against the customer's complaint and if the customer's complaint is validated, the product will be sent back to the seller and debit would be marked to the seller's account.

If Paytm feels that the products received at the RPC are not in a condition to be sent back the seller, the product will not be sent back to the seller and NO debit will be marked to the seller's account.

Paytm's decision, in either case, shall be treated as final.
<h2> 1.2 How do I know if my shipment will go to the RPC?</h2>
It is Paytm’s prerogative to decide which shipments will go through the RPC. If your shipment is assigned to the RPC, you will get the following content in your email with ‘Yes’ mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column:

“

This is to inform you that as per our logistics partner’s report, following items have been picked from the customer for return. Please find below summary of the picked items.
<table width="633">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="64"><strong>REVERSE COURIER</strong></td>
<td width="61"><strong>AWB NO</strong></td>
<td width="73"><strong>ORDER NO</strong></td>
<td width="61"><strong>ITEM ID</strong></td>
<td width="66"><strong>ITEM NAME</strong></td>
<td width="95"><strong>QUANTITY</strong></td>
<td width="75"><strong>PICKED DATE</strong></td>
<td width="117"><strong>RPC ASSIGNED</strong></td>
<td width="21">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;

“

If ‘No’ is mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column, then that particular shipment will not go through the RPC. Such shipments will be sent directly to the merchant’s address.

A ‘RPC Assigned’ flag will also be visible to the merchant on the seller panel if the shipment is assigned to the RPC.
<h2>1.3   How much time will be taken by the RPC for QC?</h2>
At RPC, every item will be quality checked thoroughly to validate customer complaint. The RPC will take a maximum of <strong>72 hours</strong> to process the shipments.
<h2>1.4   What if my item is ‘QC failed’ at RPC?</h2>
‘QC failed or QC rejected’ implies that Paytm felt that the product was not in a condition to be sent back to the merchant.

If the item is QC failed at RPC, we will not send the item back to the merchant and the item will be liquidated from the RPC. The status of such items will be shown as ‘Liquidated’ in the ‘Returns’ tab of Seller panel. No debit will be marked to the merchant in such cases.

The following communication shall go to the merchant in this case:

“

We have found that the following product that was returned by the customer, was not in a condition to be sent back to you and hence is being retained by Paytm. No debit will be marked to your account for this product.
<table width="492">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="105"><strong>Order No</strong></td>
<td width="97"><strong>Item Id</strong></td>
<td width="116"><strong>Name</strong></td>
<td width="173"><strong>Rejection  Date</strong></td>
<td width="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="105">xxxx</td>
<td width="97">xxxx</td>
<td width="116">Sample Product</td>
<td width="173">xxxx</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="105">“

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;</td>
<td width="97">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="116">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="173">&nbsp;</td>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2>1.5   What if my item is ‘QC passed’ at RPC?</h2>
‘QC passed or QC accepted’ implies that the customer’s complaint was genuine. Such shipments will be sent back to the seller. Shipping details of such shipments will be communicated to the seller once the shipments are dispatched from the RPC.

A debit will be marked to the seller’s account in such cases once the shipment is delivered.

The following communication shall go to the merchant in this case:

“

The following items returned by the customer have been quality checked at RPC. We have found that the customer's complaint was valid and hence the product is being sent back to you.

&nbsp;
<table width="570">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="102"><strong>COURIER</strong>

<strong>PARTNER</strong></td>
<td width="79"><strong>AWB NO</strong></td>
<td width="63"><strong>ORDER NO</strong></td>
<td width="61"><strong>ITEM ID</strong></td>
<td width="61"><strong>ITEM NAME</strong></td>
<td width="83"><strong>QUANTITY</strong></td>
<td width="122"><strong>SHIPPED DATE</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="102">XXXX</td>
<td width="79">XXXXX</td>
<td width="63">XXXX</td>
<td width="61">XXXX</td>
<td width="61">XXXX</td>
<td width="83">XXXX</td>
<td width="122">XXXX</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
“
<h2>1.6   What if I want my shipment to be assigned to an RPC?</h2>
The prerogative of mapping a merchant to the RPC/sending a shipment to the RPC shall lie with Paytm. A merchant can raise a request to process his/her shipments through the RPC via merchant helpdesk (email: <a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</a>) but Paytm’s decision in this regard shall be final.
<h2>1.7   When will I receive my product if it is QC passed?</h2>
Once the Item has passed the quality check and has been shipped from RPC, the merchant will get a notification about the shipments dispatched through an email. The merchant should receive such item(s) at their warehouse within 21 days of reverse pickup from the customer.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Modes Of Payments</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/modes-of-payments/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 06:00:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=364</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Payment Modes</b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As per the rules of RBI payment will be credited in the seller’s bank account in the same way the amount has been paid by the customer, the payment mode can be (COD+Wallet+Prepaid) the sum total of all which will be credited in the seller’s bank account for any order specific.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payment will happen through One97’s three different bank accounts(Escrow, Nodal and Current-- as per RBI compliance, in which ratio the money received from customer) in merchant’ s registered one bank account. Paytm will share payment details and UTR numbers of all 3 different mode payouts.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If customer returned the product and we already paid to merchant on the basis of delivered order. We reverse the same amount which we paid to merchant earlier.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payment will be done on the basis of delivered/Returned orders and after delivery payment will be released within 7 days.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For any queries regarding payments merchant will write to merchant.helpdesk@paytm., the complete details related to his query or type of issue.</span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How do I resolve the different issues regarding payments?</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/how-do-i-resolve-the-different-issues-regarding-payments/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 06:02:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=367</guid>

	<item>
		<title>Combo / Freebies Related</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/combo-freebies-related/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:00:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=389</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Enhance your sale by following the best practices to sell products as combos and Freebies </b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear Seller,</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As Paytm is growing, we continuously ensure to keep you updated with our monthly newsletter!</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this issue, we focus on how to present and  put combo and freebies for sale to reach out to 10 crore customers on Paytm.</span>

&nbsp;

<b>Selling Combos </b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a Paytm seller, you are free to sell a set of goods as a single unit with a combined price of combo to buyer. Selling combos is a great way of increasing sales by offering best offers for the customers. A simple example of a combo could be a set of T-shirts being sold at a combined price. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here is an example:</span>

&nbsp;

<b>Seller liabilities to sell a combo</b>

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The MRP should be the total sum of the individual component of the combo. For example in the above image, the MRP of the combo of 2 T-shirts is Rs. 1000 and the MRP of individual T-shirt is Rs. 500 each.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the components in the combo do not carry any MRP individually, then the seller is required to pack them as a single unit. This single unit should be carrying a valid MRP label representing the MRP of the combo.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In all other cases, the seller has to mention the individual MRPs of the component in the combo product description on the product listing page. He also has to ensure that each component carries the individual MRP label.</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Selling Freebies</b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a seller you might offer freebies with your products. Freebies are different from combos as in a Freebie the price charged is only for the base product and the name indicates a ‘free’ component is added to the purchase of the customer.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">See the example:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">BUY 1 Get 1 FREE offer, where a person gets a free T-shirt on top of the purchase of a T-shirt. </span>

&nbsp;

<b>Seller liabilities to sell a Freebie</b>

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The MRP of the listing should not include the MRP of the freebie. In the above image the MRP of the listing is Rs. 500 while the sum of the MRPs of the base product and the freebie is Rs. 1000.</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">It is recommended that you mention the individual MRPs of the base product as well as the freebie in the product description. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Violation of the above mentioned guidelines is considered as a malpractice on the part of the seller and Paytm reserves all rights to penalize the seller for any violation of these guidelines.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case of any questions on such combos and freebies initiatives from your side, please reach out to our seller helpdesk at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk.com@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk.com@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or your category contact. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note, that if any seller is found not following the above guidelines then is subjected to severe penal and legal action from Paytm.</span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Inventory Management</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/inventory-management/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:01:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=391</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Inventory management is an essential activity involved in any business and requires

for availability of sufficient amount of products in optimal quantities. So, make

efforts to maintain sufficient and ample stock at all times as this would help in

efficient control over inventory management and in turn reap great returns.

Maintaining an ideal inventory management system is also a pivotal tool to drive

your sales and achieve great success in eCommerce.You can target good sales if

you manage your product inventory efficiently.To boost sales and to prevent

situations like ‘Out of stock’ and products getting completely ‘Sold Out’ follow below

measures.

A. Averting Low stock situations :

1. Make sure that you have sufficient inventory.

2. Avert procurement delay from suppliers.

3. Plan accordingly for a promotional activity.

4. Take care of seasonal fluctuations and requirement demand

B. Factors for Managing inventory:

1. Ability to forecast future sales accurately: For sales forecast, take care of the

average past sales, expected future sales growth and sales fluctuations like

promotional activities and seasonal variations.

2. Ordering concepts: Sufficient stock should be maintained keeping

procurement delays and sudden high demand in mind. Keep a track on

number of days the inventory will last so new and the right quantity of

orders could be placed timely.

C. Stock Keeping Unit(SKU) Updation : Always update SKU whenever new stock

is added or a product’s price changes. You can update inventory in two following

ways:

i) Single SKU updation: Single SKU update is used when you change details of the

catalogue for only one single product. In Catalogue, you will select single product

and update for its change in price, MRP, quantity or any other field if any.

ii) Bulk SKU updation : Bulk updation is used to update SKU for multiple products

in a single go. To execute this, select ALL Tab-Product Details and then select the

products for which you need to update the SKU and download the CSV file of the

selected products. Open the downloaded file, make necessary changes in the fields,

save as a CSV file and upload this new file of catalog updation.

Maintaining enough stock and regular catalogue updation is essential from time to

time for effectively managing a inventory. This will also surely attract customers to

come,browse and purchase your products. In case, if you come across any issue or

need any assistance while uploading, updating CSV file or while managing your

inventory then we are just a click away at merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com .]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Pack It Smart</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/pack-it-smart/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:03:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=393</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Pack right for safe and sound product delivery:</b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Neat, careful and smart packaging not just helps in business and brand promotion but also attracts customers to come again and purchase from you. Pleasing and perfectly packed items will be liked by customers and would reach safe and sound on their destination.Not only this, it would lessen the chances of product refund as the item would be delivered safely to the customer. Hence, at all times great care must be taken while packing a product that you sell on the marketplace as it the first impression that you leave on the customer. So, let's go through general packing guidelines that need to be followed for any product as it goes through a tough journey before reaching its final destination.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Before packing a product the first step is to identify that in which category does it fall.The major categories a product could be classified are:</span>

&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li><b>A) General category and</b></li>
	<li><b>B) Fragile category</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">General category products are books, cosmetics, apparels, selected home &amp; kitchen items, pen drives, memory cards, etc.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Fragile category products are the products that are delicate and need to be handled carefully and include glassware, laptops,wall clocks, breakable toys,frames, hookahs, hand made products, etc</span>

&nbsp;

<b>Packing</b> <b>a Product</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> :Make sure you always adhere to these basic packing guidelines before shipping an item.</span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Make use of strong material to keep the product safe from scratches and to prevent damage from outside.</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cushion delicate and  fragile product from inside with bubble wrapping or padding so it does not move and does not break when in transit. </span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Use tapes liberally on joints and edges. </span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Use ‘Fragile’ sticker if  the product is fragile, breakable or delicate. </span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Labelling a Product</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Labelling plays equally important role and gives entire details of the order when you ship it. Make sure it includes the following :</span>

&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Clear shipping label that is stick on the pack. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please make sure that label,invoice are not wrinkled and all details along with barcode are </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">clearly visible.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Remember to add all other details and necessary documents.</span></li>
</ol>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Enhance your sale by following the best practices to sell products as combos and Freebies </b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear Seller,</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As Paytm is growing, we continuously ensure to keep you updated with our monthly newsletter!</span>

</ul>

	<item>
		<title>Stages</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/stages/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:08:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=398</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Stages are the order related status that the Seller sees on his Seller Panel.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Order States: Forward Process </span></strong>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pending Acknowledgement </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this state, the seller receives the order request. The seller can check the availability of inventory one last time before accepting the order.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pending Shipment: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this state, the seller has accepted the order. The order is yet to be packed.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shipment created: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The seller packs the order according to pre decided guidelines. Invoices are attached to the package. The intimation for the order goes to the courier partner as well.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Manifest Created </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The final list of products to be shipped is tabulated and invoices are printed out and attached to the order. The delivery partner collects the package from the seller shop or warehouse. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shipped </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The order is scanned and shipped to the customer from the delivery partner warehouse.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Delivered</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this state the delivery partner delivers the product to the customer. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">SEED </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">SEED centers are Paytm owned centers. In case some pin codes are non serviceable and it is difficult for courier partners to reach these sellers, SEEDs are established. The merchants deliver their products to these centers. Then the courier partners collect the orders from these SEED centers and continue the delivery process. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">SEED scan – When the order reaches the SEED from the merchants </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">SEED shipped – When the courier partner collects the order from the SEED.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Average Time Spent on States (Forward)</span>
<table>
<tbody>

&nbsp;

<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Order States: Reverse Process</strong></span>
<ol>
	<li>Return Requested: In this stage, the customer has raised a return request for the order. It marks the beginning of the return flow.</li>
	<li>Return Rejected: The return request of the customer is rejected which might be due to some pre-defined reason. this stage leads to a closure of the returns process for the order.</li>
	<li>Return Accepted: The return request is accepted in this stage and the courier partner (in case the Seller is LMD) is intimated of this.</li>
	<li>Return Picked: The stage arrives once the courier partner has picked up the parcel from the customer's premise. The Seller gets a notification at this stage.</li>
	<li>Received at RPC: This stage marks the parcel reaching one of the Paytm's Reverse Processing Centers (RPCs) for quality check purpose.</li>
	<li>Shipped From RPC: This stage occurs once the product has passed the quality checks at the assigned RPC and has been dispatched to the Seller.</li>
	<li>Liquidated: It marks the phase when the returned product fails the quality checks at the assigned RPC and is sent for liquidation. This represents the closure of the return process.</li>
	<li>Return Delivered: Once the parcel gets delivered back to the Seller, the status/ stage changes to Return Delivered. This marks the end of the returns flow.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>DTO &amp; RTO</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/rto-process-policies/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:10:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=403</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="text-decoration: underline;">DTO (Delivered to Origin)</span>

These are the normal return cases where the customer returns the product (against a predefined reason) to the seller. These deliveries are called Open Box Cases since the customer (in majority of the cases) has opened the parcel before requesting a reverse pickup.

For the sellers availing Paytm's LMD services, the courier partner will check the actual product against the return reason at the time of reverse pickup to ensure that only geniune requests are processed for return. The sellers are therefore liable to accept any return which comes via this route, irrespective of the product condition. The sellers are also required to take photographic evidence of the returned open box parcel and the product inside.

<span style="text-decoration: underline;">RTO (Return to Origin)</span>

Situation when the shipped goods is delivered back to the origin without customer even receiving it. This can happen in the following situations:-

 Non-availability of the customer at the shipping address

Customer cancels the order while it is still in transit (although in such cases, the courier still makes an attempt to deliver the product)

The seller has to bear the returns logistic cost in case he is availing the Paytm LMD service. If the Seller is a Non-LMD, Paytm won't share any cost related liabilities for reverse logistics.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

		<title>SEED</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/seed/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:39:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=408</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[SEED

SEED (Speedy Efficient Express Delivery) centers acts as consolidation points where a partner agency will gather all packets that need to be handed over to the courier partner from the merchants in specified PIN codes.
For this, the partner agency does a physical point-to-point pick up thru its own workforce.
Once the shipments for a day are consolidated in the SEED center, partner agency will be responsible for sorting &amp; handing the packets to respective courier partners

SEED centers helps to overcome the following challenges:
Reduce cancellation of orders since no courier partners picks up from merchant location
Reduce cancellation of orders since courier partner took long to visit a particular merchant since there were very less no. of packets]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>LMD v/s NLMD</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/lmd-vs-nlmd/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:41:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=410</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Last Mile Delivery (LMD)</b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm offers end to end logistic service called Last Mile Delivery  to its merchants via the network of courier partners. Seller’s opting for this service enjoy the following benefits:-</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flat courier charges for Pan india (details can be found here)</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No hassle of tracking the status of delivery as the Paytm system automatically takes care of this</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Automated and timely payouts</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Network providing large coverage of pincodes</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Non Last Mile Delivery (NLMD)</b>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sellers not opting for Paytm’s Last Mile Delivery (LMD) service have to fulfill the logistics related requirements on their own. This system has the following benefits for the sellers:-</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Decide upon the pincode you want to serve</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Closer to the customer thereby better understanding of their needs</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller has the freedom to chose his means of delivery and thus can save on charges </span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In order to opt for LMD service, Sellers are required to drop their request to merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Paytm Packaging</title>

		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 10:45:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=414</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Paytm’s General Shipping Orders- Guidelines</b>

&nbsp;

Use only Paytm packing material that is available at subsidized rates mentioned below

&nbsp;
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><b>Packing Material </b></td>
<td><b>Size</b></td>
<td><b>Charges</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Poly Bag</td>
<td>6 X 7 inches</td>
<td>Rs 2/- Per envelope (subsidised)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Poly Bag</td>
<td>12 X 14 inches</td>
<td>Rs 3/- Per envelope (subsidised)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Poly Bag</td>
<td>14 X 17 inches</td>
<td>Rs 5/- Per envelope (subsidised)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>PAcking Tape</td>
<td>Not Applicable</td>
<td>No Charges</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Ensure the print quality of pack slip is good and barcode should be clearly visible and scannable.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Packaging slip should be pasted on flat surface of the  product ,if the product packaging is in round shape then paste pack slip horizontally and Pack slip must be horizontally covered with transparent tape in both of the case .</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Seal the invoice pouch of poly bag to avoid  losing Packing Slip.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>It is mandatory to keep a copy of invoice inside the packaging / Box.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>The Paytm brand tape must be used for sealing the product. (On the open-able area like on box and poly bag flap).</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Other competitor/portal packaging material <b>must not </b>be used for Paytm orders and vice versa. Such packets will not be accepted by our logistics partners.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Paytm branded poly bag should be used for the Paytm orders but merchant can use non transparent tamper proof poly bag in case of size mismatch with the product.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Fragile and handle with care sticker must be used on the shipment to raise alert to the courier partner for fragile and breakable shipments.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Please use link for ordering <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/paytm.com/forms/d/10__UHXvKE2O2GasPZPFaiwlZQ0jR4bbuOOL6TE1hV2A/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">packing material</a> requirement, just ensure that all such requests will be closed in 7-10 days from the day requested so kindly keep sufficient packing material stock with you always for at least 15 days.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Transparent tape should be pasted on Address of customer on packing slip.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>Packaging of products should be transit worthy; Paytm will not be responsible for any damages occurred due to non-transit worthy packaging.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

Note: It is mandatory to use either Paytm Tape or Paytm Poly Bag else shipment will be considered invalid by our courier partners. Also never use other portal packing materials.

&nbsp;

<b>Ordering Packaging Material</b>

&nbsp;

Please use link for ordering <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/paytm.com/forms/d/10__UHXvKE2O2GasPZPFaiwlZQ0jR4bbuOOL6TE1hV2A/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">packing material</a> requirement, just ensure that all such requests will be closed in 7-10 days from the day requested so kindly keep sufficient packing material stock with you always for at least 15 days.

	<item>
		<title>Shipping Fee Calculator</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/shipping-fee-calculator/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Oct 2015 06:48:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=376</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Logistics Charges

The charges are applicable only for LMD merchants. The logistic charges are calculated by taking the

higher of volumetric weight and the original weight of the shipment. The volumetric weight is

calculated by simply dividing the volume (in cubic cm) by a factor of 5 which is then compared with the

actual weight in grams. This weight is then multiplied by the logistics rate as below:-

Charges

 For BD surface, it will be 20/- for every 1kg, where minimum charge is Rs.100 for initial 5kg

For example

weight charges

4 Kg Rs 100

10 kg Rs. 200

12 kg Rs. 240

 For other shippers:

Logistic will be 45/- for every 500 gms , where minimum charge is Rs.45

For example

weight charges

2 kg Rs. 180

250gms Rs.45

NOTE: These charges are exclusive of taxes.

Final Logistics is deducted on weight of fulfillment created and then amount is equally divided on

each item based on weight of individual item.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Shipping Fee Calculation</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/shipping-fee-calculation/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 07:40:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=425</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Logistics Charges</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The charges are applicable only for LMD merchants. The logistic charges are calculated by taking the higher of volumetric weight and the original weight of the shipment.  The volumetric weight is calculated by simply dividing the volume (in cubic cm) by a factor of 5 which is then compared with the actual weight in grams.  This weight is then multiplied by the logistics rate as below:-</span>

<b>Charges</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For BD surface, it will be 20/- for every 1kg, where minimum charge is Rs.100 for initial 5kg</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">For example</span>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">weight</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">charges</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">4 Kg</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs 100</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">10 kg</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 200</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">12 kg</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 240</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For other shippers:</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Logistic will be 45/- for every 500 gms , where minimum charge is Rs.45</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">For example</span>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">weight</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">charges</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">2 kg</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 180</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">250gms</span></td>
<td><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs.45</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<b>NOTE:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> These charges are exclusive of taxes.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Final Logistics is deducted on weight of fulfillment created and then amount is equally divided on each item based on weight of individual item.</span>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>SS vs NSS</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/ss-vs-nss/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 07:48:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=428</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Shippable Service (SS)</span></strong>

SS represent the Pincodes which are covered among the network of Paytm's Last Mile Delivery Service (LMD). Paytm will provide seamless forward and reverse logistics services to the SS Pincodes for the sellers availing the LMD services.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Non-Shippable Services (NSS)</span></strong>

NSS represents the Pincodes which are not covered among the network of Paytm's Last Mile Delivery Service (LMD). Seller will have to self serve themselves for logistics related requirements in NSS areas.]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<title>Cancellation Process</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/cancellation-process-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 07:52:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=433</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Cancellation represents a state when the orders needs to be terminated due to one of the following reasons:-

&nbsp;
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;

<strong>Cancellation Reason</strong></td>
<td><strong>Cancellation due to</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>SLA Breach</strong></td>
<td><strong>Merchant**</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Out Of Stock</strong></td>
<td><strong>Merchant**</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Manifest Not shared</strong></td>
<td><strong>Merchant**</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Poor Packaging</strong></td>
<td><strong>Merchant**</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>NSS Orders</td>
<td>Admin (Paytm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Tech Issue</td>
<td>Admin (Paytm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Catalog Issue</td>
<td>Admin (Paytm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Wrong Pricing</td>
<td>Admin (Paytm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Lost / Damage in Transit</td>
<td>Logistics partner</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Pickup Issue</td>
<td>Logistics partner</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Fraud Order</td>
<td>Admin (Paytm)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
The Cancellation Process is as below:-

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-434" src="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/cancellation-Process.png" alt="cancellation Process" width="1264" height="188" />]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Commonly Used Terms</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/commonly-used-terms/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 08:59:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=438</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Commonly Used Terms</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span>
<ol>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Order ID</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – An order id is generated every time an order is placed by a customer. This order id is unique and is used to identify the order in case of a dispute. A single order id may contain multiple item IDs.  </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Product ID</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – A product id is unique id for a product. The PID is unique for a merchant and product. This means that the same product being sold at 2 different merchants will have 2 different PIDs.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
</ol>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ul>
	<li><b><b>Merchant ID – </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">A unique number given to every merchant. </span><b>

</b></b></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Item ID </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">– An item id is an id given to a product when an order is created. It is contained within an order id. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Merchant SKU ID</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – Merchant SKU id is the id given to a product by the merchant. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Paytm SKU ID</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – Paytm SKU id is an id given by Paytm to a product since the Merchant SKU id may be random and not different for different merchants </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Category ID</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – An id given to a category </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Fulfillment ID </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">- Fulfillment ID is used to track individual packets. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">For example - if an order contains 2 power banks and one mobile phone which the customer ordered together. Now suppose that the merchant decided to pack the power banks and phone separately.  Both the packs will have the same Order ID, MID and delivery address. But to track individual the packets, separate Fulfillment IDs are generated given to each pack to track them separately. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">This fulfillment ID is then mapped to the AWB number which is used by the delivery partner.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>AWB number </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">– Air Way Bill number is used to track the order and know exactly where the order is in the delivery process. It is used by the delivery partners. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Manifest ID </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">– The manifest for multiple items is processed together. These items all have the same manifest ID. All items with the same manifest ID are given to one courier partner together. So the manifest ID is used to track the ‘package’ of multiple items given to the courier partner all with different order IDs, fulfillment ID, invoices, but the same Manifest IDs </span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Merchant Track ID (</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">On clicking Fulfillment ID) - This ID is part of the invoice number for a particular order. Gives information about how many orders the merchant has serviced till then. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Shipment ID – </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Same as Fulfillment ID</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">LMD &amp; non LMD</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">SS and NSS</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">RPC</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Return policy ID</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Marketing Commission</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transfer Price</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">PG Commission</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller panel</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Manifest</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seller Onboarding</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Brand Authorization</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Delisting</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">API integration</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tagging</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Helpdesk</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Order Processing Team</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">SPOC</span></li>
</ol>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Commonly Used Terms</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/commonly-used-terms-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 09:24:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=441</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">Commonly Used Terms</p>

<ol>
<ol>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Order ID</b> – An order id is generated every time an order is placed by a customer. This is a unique identifier for any order placed at Paytm. Since a single order might comprise of multiple items so an order ID might contain multiple Item IDs.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Product ID</b> – A product id is unique identifier for a product - merchant combination. Same product being sold by different merchants will have different PIDs depending on the merchant.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b><b><b>Merchant ID – </b></b></b>A unique number given to every merchant.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Item ID </b>– An item id is an id given to a product when an order is created. It is contained within an order id.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Merchant SKU ID</b> – Merchant SKU id is the id given to a product by the merchant.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Paytm SKU ID</b> – Paytm SKU id is an id given by Paytm to a product since the Merchant SKU id are generated by the Seller and may coincide.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Category ID</b> – An id given to a category.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Fulfillment ID </b>- Fulfillment ID is used to track each packet shipped individually. For example - if a single order comprises of two power banks and one mobile phone and the Seller decides to ship each Item individually then although each of the packet will have the same Order ID, MID and delivery address but to track the individual packets, separate Fulfillment IDs are generated. These fulfillment ID are then mapped to the AWB number which are used by the delivery partner.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>AWB number </b>– Air Way Bill number is used to track the order and know exactly where the order is in the delivery process. It is used by the delivery partners.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Manifest ID </b>– The manifest for multiple orders is processed together. These orders all have the same manifest ID. All orders with the same manifest ID are given to one courier partner together. So the manifest ID is used to track the ‘package’ of multiple items given to the courier partner all with different order IDs, fulfillment ID, invoices, but the same Manifest IDs.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><b>Shipment ID – </b>This is same as Fulfillment ID.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;">LMD &amp; non -LMD- Fulfilment service provided by Paytm is called last Mile Delivery (LMD). You may read more about this <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/lmd-vs-nlmd/">here</a>.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>SS and NSS - </strong>Shipable Service are geographical areas which are covered under the LMD coverage area and returns pickup areas. You can read more about this <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/ss-vs-nss/">here.</a></li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>RPC - </strong>Paytm has recently introduced its state of the art Return Processing Centers (RPCs) across the country. You can read more about RPCs<a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/rpc/"> here</a>.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;">Return Policy ID- Every item listed on Paytm is listed against a particular return policy which is identified by a return Policy Number. This in turn defines the return related terms and conditions for the customer. You may like to read more about the return policy <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/return-policies/">here</a>.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;">Marketing Commission: The percentage commission of the Selling Price charged by Paytm marketplace for every order is called the marketing Commission. Details regarding this can be found <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/commissions-2/">here</a>.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Transfer Price</strong>: At times, Paytm may decide the Selling Price of a particular listing belonging to a seller. In such cases, the seller decides the Transfer Price which will get transferred to him/her as payout once the product gets sold.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>PG Commission:</strong> This is the percentage commission levied on the money which the customer is transacting for buying the product. You may read more about this <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/various-fee/">here.</a>.</li>
	<li style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Seller Panel: </strong>This is the interface which is used by the seller in order to upload his products , manage his listings, process orders and perform other vital tasks related to a seller. You can learn the use of Seller panel <a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/training/">here</a>.</li>
</ol>
</ol>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Various Fee</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/various-fee/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Oct 2015 07:49:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=473</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Logistics Payout and Commission</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Items finalized at the time of Merchant On-boarding for Merchant Payouts- </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.  Catalogue</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.  Marketplace Commission </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.  SKU wise price </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">4.  LMD</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">5.  Delivery Charges </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">6.  PG charges</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Catalogue</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Catalogue is the product description provided by the merchant for the items merchant is willing to sell on Paytm market place. These products can be from a single category or can spread across multiple categories.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Market Place Commission</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Market Place commission is the fee charged by Paytm from Merchants for selling their products on Paytm Market Place. These commissions can either be fixed fee on item level or % of selling price on category, merchant and brand level.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Types of Commission Definition in System:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transfer Price</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Commission on % of Selling Price</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transfer</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Price</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Fixed fee model on item level is called commission on </span><b>Transfer Price</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. For items listed under Transfer price commission model, selling price is decided by the respective category team / Merchant SPOC considering the delivery charges and profit margins for Paytm. System level check for the same is set at </span><b>Transfer Price cannot be more than Selling Price</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Transfer Price commission model is </span><b>not much encouraged within the system.</b>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Commission on % of Selling Price</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Default commission are % of selling price on category, merchant and brand level. For each category there is a default commission %already defined and merchants joining those category are assigned these default commission %.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For merchant payout, following fallback sequence of checks are done for Commission deduction and releasing merchant payout:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product Level</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant + Category  + Brand</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant + Category</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Category</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">SKU wise Price</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">SKU wise price list is the price on which item is sold to the customer. Promo code can be applied on the order level. SKU level prices are decided by the respective merchant (except for the merchants on Transfer Price commission model). </span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">LMD</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchants can opt for choosing option of either delivering items on their own or through logistic partner tie-ups managed by Paytm. Based on the LMD / Non-LMD merchant, logistic charges are deducted from the Merchant.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Delivery Charges</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Delivery charges are deducted from the merchant payout for LMD enabled customers. By default </span><b>Rs45 per 500</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> gm are charged from the merchant. Another way of calculating delivery charges is by calculating volumetric weight. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volumetric weight = L *B * H / 5</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If Product weight is more than 5Kg, item is delivered by Bluedart Surface and charged at Rs20/kg with minimum charges of Rs200 for 10kg.</span>

&nbsp;
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">PG charges</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payment Gateway charges are deducted from merchant for all transactions at default rate of </span><b>3.03% of selling price</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Pack it right to ensure safe product delivery</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=490</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=325</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400">Neat, careful and smart packaging not just helps in business and brand promotion but also attracts customers to come again and purchase from you. Pleasing and perfectly packed items will be liked by customers and would reach safe and sound on their destination.Not only this, it would lessen the chances of product refund as the item would be delivered safely to the customer. Hence, at all times great care must be taken while packing a product that you sell on the marketplace as it the first impression that you leave on the customer. So, let's go through general packing guidelines that need to be followed for any product as it goes through a tough journey before reaching its final destination.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400">Before packing a product the first step is to identify that in which category does it fall.The major categories a product could be classified are:</span>

<b>A) General category and</b>

<b>B) Fragile category</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400">General category products are books, cosmetics, apparels, selected home &amp; kitchen items, pen drives, memory cards, etc.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400">Fragile category products are the products that are delicate and need to be handled carefully and include glassware, laptops,wall clocks, breakable toys,frames, hookahs, hand made products, etc.</span>

<b>Packing</b> <b>a Product</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> :Make sure you always adhere to these basic packing guidelines before shipping an item.</span>
<ul>
	<li>Make use of strong material to keep the product safe from scratches and to prevent damage from outside.</li>
	<li>Cushion delicate and  fragile product from inside with bubble wrapping or padding so it does not move and does not break when in transit.</li>
	<li>Use tapes liberally on joints and edges.</li>
	<li>Use ‘Fragile’ sticker if  the product is fragile, breakable or delicate.</li>
</ul>
<b>Labeling a Product</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Labeling plays equally important role and gives entire details of the order when you ship it. Make sure it includes the following :</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Clear shipping label that is stick on the pack. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Please make sure that label,invoice are not wrinkled and all details along with bar-code are </span> <span style="font-weight: 400">clearly visible.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Remember to add all other details and necessary documents.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400">If you wish to learn step by step packing procedure for a particular product category then please refer to <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/#/trainingCentre" target="_blank">Seller Panel </a></span><span style="font-weight: 400">. We assure you that if you follow these packing guidelines your customer requests for product return would drop to a large extent and cases of breakage and refunds will also decline. This means your business would grow more as you will sell more with Paytm!</span>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>490</wp:post_id>

	<item>
		<title>Tips to boost sales on eCommerce marketplace</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=491</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=328</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400">A great number of factors come in help to boost online sales of product. With</span><strong>?????.</strong><span style="font-weight: 400">number of customers to serve, Paytm offers solutions and support to its sellers to sell and grow at a rapid pace on one of the largest marketplace in the country. If you follow these top ten rules then for sure your sales figure will increase enormously and business will expand manifold in a very short span of time.</span>
<ol>
	<li><b>Promo Participation</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Promotion of products help sell huge number of products during promo period. From time to time Paytm keeps sellers informed for upcoming and available promotional sales in different categories wherein seller participation would bear desired </span> <span style="font-weight: 400">results.To make use of promotional sales one must keep an eye on the </span> <span style="font-weight: 400">seller website and should regularly go through the newsletters received in emails.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
	<li><b>Catalog Updation: </b><span style="font-weight: 400">Product catalog represents your product on the website and is crucial to attract and influence buyers to make a decision for buying. You must update catalog on regular basis and add new products to keep the buyer engaged in  purchasing products. Keep these following points in mind to attract new customers while retaining old customers for great sales.</span></li>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Update your catalog regularly </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Add new items on a regular basis</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Offer best price for items that you sell</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Sell products in different price range so that buyers have several option to buy from. Sell products in low, medium and high price range on the website to attract different buyers . </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">From time to time offer discounts when buyer makes a multiple purchase</span></li>
</ul>
<ol start="3">
	<li><b>Use good quality images:</b></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400">            People buy products when they see their images and hence good quality images are another important key factor to boost your sales                   figure. Keep below points in mind when you capture a product’s image:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Show product's detailed view in image.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Have images taken from different angles.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Upload sharp and clear images.</span></li>
</ul>
<ol start="4">
	<li><b>Safe &amp; smart packaging:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> This is one of the key features for boosting product sale. For each product category Paytm has a complete list of Packaging guidelines in Seller Panel. Make sure you adhere to these packaging guidelines for a safe, secure and timely delivery of the purchased item. Safe packaging also reduce chances of 'breaking' while item is in transit. Also offer free shipping on the products listed for specific price so customers happily add these to their shopping cart without worrying for paying extra shipping cost for the order.As far as metropolitan cities are concerned remain committed to same day or 1 day product delivery.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol start="5">
	<li><b>Timely dispatch and delivery:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Products purchased and packed should be dispatched by reliable logistic in the fastest time possible for quick delivery. Quick and fast dispatch would also result in timely delivery at buyer's end. Timely and quick delivery will please buyer </span> <span style="font-weight: 400">and he would like to shop again and again from you.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol start="6">
	<li><b>Sell flawless items: </b><span style="font-weight: 400">At all times ensure the product delivery is safe and the product reaches buyer in safe, complete and working condition. Refrain from sending faulty or fake products and make sure you re-check products before dispatching it.This would for sure help you get buyers’ trust and you can expect them come to you to make their future purchases from you.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol start="6">
	<li><b> Sell products at right price:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Sell products at reasonable price and offer best services for it. Look forward for long term association   with buyers by retaining them and do not focus on short term profits by selling products at very high price.</span></li>
</ol>
<ol start="8">
	<li><b>Have enough stocks in inventory: </b><span style="font-weight: 400">Sufficient amount of  products are required to run any business and do great online business. Buyers would not be attracted and inclined to purchase products if they have very less or limited choices when they come to shop from you. So make sure you always have enough stock of items to fulfill large number of orders  in short time.</span></li>
</ol>
9<b>.Customer trust &amp; satisfaction:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Customer trust and satisfaction is guaranteed if you follow all above mentioned points. For sure                  if you provide great quality products, ensure timely delivery, sell goods at a fair</span> <span style="font-weight: 400">price, offer free shipping and services like timely                          replacement then you will get customer trust and satisfaction which will retain them as your customers and will also result in                                enhancing your sales.</span>
<ol start="10">
	<li><b>Follow Marketplace Rules: </b><span style="font-weight: 400">You must comply and adhere to all the rules listed on <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Seller Panel</a>. These rules help you with catalog, packaging and all other details that are required for right listing of </span> <span style="font-weight: 400">products.</span><span style="font-weight: 400">Follow all listed selling policies and always refrain from unethical business practices for instance do not ship empty boxes , do not sell incomplete products and  fake products to customer.</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Payment Issues</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/payment-issues/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Oct 2015 06:56:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=568</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<ol>
	<li><b> What is the payment procedure of any merchant?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payout cycle thrice in a week (M, W, F) on the basis of delivered orders on system. Payment against this payout will reflect in merchant accounts within 7 days after delivery of product.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For example order delivered till Sunday payout will be done for these orders in Monday cycle and order delivered between Monday to Tuesday payout will be done for these orders in Wednesday cycle and order delivered between Wednesday to Thursday payout will be done for these orders in Friday cycle. </span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="2">
	<li><b> How and when a merchant get paid?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payment will happen through One97’s three different bank accounts (Escrow, Nodal and Current-- as per RBI compliance, in which ratio the money received from customer) in merchant’ s registered one bank account. Paytm will share payment details and UTR numbers of all 3 different mode payouts.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="3">
	<li><b> Reverse payments procedure?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If customer returned the product and we already paid to merchant on the basis of delivered order. We reverse the same amount which we paid to merchant earlier.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="4">
	<li><b> Any guidelines and policies under Payments?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Payment will be done on the basis of delivered/Returned orders and after delivery payment will be released within 7 days.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="5">
	<li><b> For any queries regarding payments, how will you resolve those issues ?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For any queries regarding payments merchant will write to </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> mentioned the complete details related to his query or type of issue.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="5">
	<li><b> When I will get the Commission Invoice?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We used to share the commission invoice with merchant on 5</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">th</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of every month. This commission invoice having the complete details of MP Commission, PG commission and logistic commission for the month.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="6">
	<li><b> How do I get TDS reimbursement?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant will submit TDS certificate to Paytm on the basis of actual TDS which shoild be deducted against Paytm commission invoices and which Merchant has deposited to government. Paytm shall reiemburse the amount of TDS amount to merchant as pper TDS certificate within 15 days from the receipt of the TDS certificate.</span>

&nbsp;
<ol start="7">
	<li><b> How do we update the bank details and email id or communication address?</b></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant will share the cancelled cheque along with authorised signature / new mail id or new address with </span><a href="mailto:merchant.onboarding@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.onboarding@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> id. New mail id and address will be updated by team. For change of bank details it will take 7 to 10 working days.</span>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Registration &amp; On-boarding Related</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/registration-on-boarding-related/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Oct 2015 06:59:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?page_id=574</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3><b>GETTING STARTED:</b></h3>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I am a seller. How can I sell my products on Paytm?</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We welcome you to excel your business on PAytm. You can start selling in by a simple registration on </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/#/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Once you complete this registration our Merchant management team will get in touch with you to help you further.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">How do I contact Paytm to become a seller? Is there a seller helpline?</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, Paytm has a complete dedicated support for sellers. Please get in touch at </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to become a Paytm seller. All sellers can contact Paytm’s helpline for 24X7 assistance by writing to </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>
<h5><span style="font-weight: 400;">In which categories can I sell products on Paytm.com?</span></h5>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can sell items in the following Stores:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Home, Electronics, Men, Women, Sports &amp; Health Home &amp; Kitchen, Baby, Kids &amp; Toys, Stationery,Gifts &amp; Sweets, Industrial Supplies and many subcategories of these Stores. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;"> I am a registered seller on Paytm platform but unable to login on the Platform.Why?</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There could be following reasons for it:</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You forgot your username and password</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The user­ID entered by you is incorrect</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You have not yet received any registration confirmation on your registered email id.</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Please follow below steps to Login and access the Seller Panel</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Go to </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://seller.paytm.com</span></a></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enter your registered email ID: xxxxxxxxx</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enter Password</span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Still, if you are not able to login then click on "Forgot Password?" to again reset your password. A confirmation email will be sent to your registered email id. Clicking on the link will allow you to again login on the Platform.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case, if you do not receive the confirmation email, then please contact merchant help­desk at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">My login is successful but I only see a blank screen with an error message.</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Please share below details at </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in order to help us fix this issue:</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User ID</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Merchant ID</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Error screenshot</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Is it possible to change basic details like display name, contact number, warehouse address and alternate details in future ?</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, this is possible. However, you have to request for the changes at </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The merchant helpdesk will verify these and update in the system.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Change in KYC and bank details:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Change in Store name: Please share the new store name and scanned copy of VAT/TIN number, the merchant helpdesk will verify it and update in the system.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Change in Company Address: Please provide the below proof to merchant helpdesk for updating details in the system.</span>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Copy of address proof</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">VAT</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Broadband Bill</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Postpaid phone bill</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rent Agreement</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Where can I find my Merchant ID (MID)?</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Please access : Settings tab -&gt;Profile sub-tab -&gt;Merchant ID (MID)</span>

&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Will I be assigned an Account Manager?</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your Account is managed by dedicated Merchant Helpdesk team that helps resolve all your queries. You can reach out to them 24 X 7 </span><a href="mailto:atmerchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">atmerchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a>

&nbsp;
<h5><span style="font-weight: 400;">Can I sell on Paytm if I do not have a website ?</span></h5>
<h5><span style="font-weight: 400;">You do not require a website to sell products on Paytm. Once you become a seller on Paytm, you will have easy access to Paytm’s Seller Panel to list and sell all your products online.</span></h5>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paytm for Sellers is here!</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-for-sellers-is-here/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2015 07:16:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=34</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is India’s largest mobile commerce platform, where over 50 million Indians have trusted us with their money and we do over 60 million transactions per month. Our mission is to be and remain the most trusted mobile commerce platform; and as we’ve never taken even a single consumer for granted the same goes for our sellers!</p>
<p dir="ltr"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/04/merchant-cover-image_blog.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="282" /></p>
<p dir="ltr">You’re the anchor of our <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">marketplace</a> as you’ve the faith in us to give them the best support and platform to grow their businesses. We believe that everyone who has a business in this country can be part of the Paytm story and we’ll help them on-boarding into the mCommerce industry, using our services to sell online to millions of customers across the country.  We re imagine eCommerce in ways that builds a more fulfilling and lasting world where we give you the right tools to be successful.</p>
<p dir="ltr">This <span class="il">blog</span> is for you, the sellers, and gives you a much needed platform to know what is happening in, around and on Paytm and our <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Seller Panel</a>. It’s makes you stay connected and keeps you updated from the very first day when you join us. You’ve not joined yet our 30,000 sellers? Get started now and <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com" target="_blank">sign up on Paytm</a>!</p>
<p dir="ltr">Not only this, we give you the latest updates for your business benefits, help you grow and promote your business. From time to time we’ve special promotions that you can utilize and in turn help you sell more in the over 500+ categories on our <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm marketplace</a>.</p>
<p dir="ltr">If you need support or want to give us feedback, then please write to us anytime at <a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com" target="_blank">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</a>! We care and love to hear from you.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So, to get to know everything about Paytm's latest happenings, infos &amp; news, keep a watch on this <span class="il">blog</span>.</p>
Happy Selling!]]></content:encoded>

	<li class="li3">Continous dedicated support</li>

		<title>Sell on Paytm!</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/sell-on-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2015 10:10:17 +0000</pubDate>
