		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1">We attract entrepreneurs across India to our hugely successful marketplace to sell online to more than 30 million users and we are adding 2 million each month! We've sellers in over 500 plus categories selling successfully on <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> from motorcycles, <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/h/electronics" target="_blank">electronics</a>,<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>jewellery, fashion, children’s toys and healthcare, home essentials, furniture, to <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/g/home-and-kitchen/home-utility/bath-accessories" target="_blank">bathroom accessories</a> and books.</p>
<p class="p1"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/04/Sell-on-Patm-1-blog.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="377" /></p>
<p class="p1">As a mobile commerce platform the future we’re chasing is one of digital money and our vision is to enable 100 million user in India transact using <a href="https://accounts.paytm.com/oauth2/authorize?theme=mp-web&amp;redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fpaytm.com%2Fshop%2Fcode&amp;is_verification_excluded=false&amp;client_id=paytm-web&amp;type=web_server&amp;scope=paytm&amp;response_type=code" target="_blank">Paytm Wallet</a> not just online, but offline, too. We are growing at an enormous pace and we're excited to have you on this journey with us! If you look to increase the sales for your business, Paytm makes it easy for you to sell online and become your own <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> success story.</p>
<p class="p1">Join 30,000 sellers today. <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">Start now</a>! It's easy with a free listing and has the fastest set up.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Seller support on Paytm</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/seller-support-on-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2015 12:04:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=76</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Becoming a <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com" target="_blank">Paytm Seller</a> is the best way to fully participate in today’s digital economy and drive sales. Now if you need support to sell on Paytm, then our merchant helpdesk got the answers for you. It is a platform to help you succeed in taking the advantage of the features and benefits that <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> offers to sellers. Our helpdesk will give you ways to improve your online operations and how to advance with Paytm your online store.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/04/Merchant_helpdesk_blogpost.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="413" /></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We provide you with the complete information about your account, catalogue, payments, returns and new developments happening at our end. No matter what issue you come across, our merchant helpdesk is one single point of contact where you can get answers to all your questions any time.</span><span class="s2">The purpose of our help desk is to provide you with a resolution to the challenge you may have come across, like how to manage your Paytm account dashboard, your  catalogue &amp; inventory, promoting your brand, or payment issues. We’re happy to help at </span><strong><span class="s3">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></strong><span class="s4">!</span></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paytm launches new Wallet &amp; Seller Apps</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-launches-new-wallet-seller-apps/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2015 08:07:23 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=81</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1">Watch <a href="https://twitter.com/vijayshekhar" target="_blank">Vijay Shekhar Sharma</a>, founder &amp; CEO of Paytm, talk about the launch details in interview with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2G6PMI0AAZI&amp;feature=youtu.be" target="_blank">CNBC</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=24&amp;v=6AbNIe97xCE" target="_blank">ZEE</a>:</p>
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2G6PMI0AAZI&feature=youtu.be[/embed]

[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=24&v=6AbNIe97xCE[/embed]
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">With the launch of our new Paytm Wallet and Seller Apps, Paytm demonstrates its commitment to mobile solutions and our capabilities in developing cutting-edge mobile applications that help users in their daily lives as well as sellers to evolve their businesses.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Did you know that our <a href="https://paytm.com/paytmcash" target="_blank">Paytm Wallet</a> is trusted by 60 million users for their mobile payments? And now we're upping that further with the launch of our new Paytm Wallet App. It's free and enables users to transfer money from one person to another fast in a few clicks, request money, securely store money online and let’s users do their shopping &amp; payments on the go. With the</span> <a href="https://paytm.com/blog/enjoy-unlimited-offers-when-you-upgrade-your-paytm-wallet/" target="_blank">KYC (Know-Your-Customer) process</a> users can transact upto Rs. 1,00,000 in a month online, otherwise the spending limit is upto Rs. 10,000.</p>
<p class="p1">Moreover our first priority is it to bring as many sellers on our platform as possible. With this large user base, we give you, the SMEs, a great opportunity to sell your products online and expand your business reach. We're adding a mobile marketplace app extra for you which has an integrated chat feature, so that buyers can bargain directly with sellers and negotiate in real time. This is an attempt by <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> to emulate real life conversations on its m-commerce platform.</p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is India’s largest mobile commerce platform and we’re aiming to bring one million sellers on our marketplace by the end of 2015. With our mobile first strategy, we do more than 60 million orders of various digital and physical goods every month. Launched in 2014, Paytm Wallet is India's dominant mobile payment service platform. As a mobile commerce platform the future we’re chasing is one of digital money and our vision is to enable 100 million users in India transact using Paytm Wallet not just online, but <a href="https://paytm.com/blog/our-new-paytm-wallet-features-are-here-transfer-money-online-or-deposit-cash/" target="_blank">offline</a> too.</span></p>

<div dir="ltr">
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">If you haven't downloaded the best wallet app yet, then try it <a href="https://paytm.com/mobile"><span class="s2">now</span></a> &amp; get started today. It’s a fun &amp; convenient way to do your online payments! And sellers, where are you?! <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/"><span class="s2">Sign up today</span></a> to go big and grow our business with India's largest m-commerce platform. </span></p>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Live Now - GoBig with Paytm</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/live-now-gobig-with-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2015 12:39:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=100</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong><a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank">GoBig</a> with <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is a platform that connects you with service providers to help you grow your online business on Paytm.</strong>

<a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/05/Go-big.jpg" alt="" width="592" height="259" /></a>

Are you set to boost your business online? Do you need catalogue support? Do require marketing services to promote your business?

Well, then <span class="il">GoBig</span> with <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is the platform for you to go to. We made  the platform for you to succeed online and to empower you more so that all of you 'go big' on Paytm.

Let’s get started with a sneak-peak to going <span class="il">big</span>. The services provided here range from catalogue services like photo shootings and image processing, blog writing, Email marketing, Facebook promotions to website designing, SEO, business services etc. <a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank"><span class="il">GoBig</span></a> is a platform between <a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank">service providers</a> and <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">seekers</a>, which is free of cost. Catering to over 200 service providers at its inception, we are surely going <span class="il">big</span> on our ways and will add more and more services for you.

So, here is your chance to <span class="il">GO BIG</span> and successful as going home is just no option!

&nbsp;

	<item>
		<title>FAQs for Sign Up at Paytm</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/faqs-for-your-eller-sign-up-at-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2015 12:58:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=104</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1"><a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> to sell to 3 Crore customers! Still questions?! We've got the answers for you here:</p>
<p class="p1"><strong>1. How do I register myself as a seller on Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Our register process is fairly simple:</span></p>

<ol class="ol2">
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">Upload your PAN, VAT/TIN, cancelled cheque and address proof in the link provided by the Paytm Business Development Associate</span></li>
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">Fill in your details in the link provided</span></li>
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">Provide your Catalog and images for upload</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="p2"><span class="s1">Once done, we'll provide you your merchant panel and login details within 2 days. You can start seeing your products going live on Paytm within a week.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><strong>2. What all products can I sell on Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">You can sell items in over 500+ categories on Paytm starting from Fashion, Electronics, Home Appliances, Automotive, Health Care, Books, Jewellry, Kitchen, Home Furnishing, Automotive and more. We're adding more categories. Please contact us to know more at merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>3. What are the charges to ‘Sell on Paytm’?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Registering at Paytm is free of any cost, our business development executives will take you live once they have your required documents and catalog with images.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>4. Who can sell on Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Any person in any part of the country who has a valid VAT/TIN, PAN, and a business with products to sell can get his products listed on Paytm.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><!--more--></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>5. If I do not have a VAT/TIN, can I still register at Paytm ?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Yes, in that case we would require a VAT undertaking from your side (duly stamped &amp; signed). There are exceptions as normally VAT/TIN isn't required for books, unstitched apparels, sarees etc. However, we take the undertaking from you in lieu of the VAT document.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>6. I do not have a current account; can I work with my savings account?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Yes, we would only require your company/proprietor stamp on the cancelled cheque and then we can register you.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>7. How does selling on Paytm work?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Selling on Paytm is very easy. First, list the products that you want to sell on Paytm's marketplace. The customer sees your product and makes a purchase. You'll receive an email to ship the product. You deliver the product to the customer and confirm the shipment. Paytm will deposit the funds into your bank account (as per the payment term) after deducting its fees.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>8. What are the commissions for working at Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">The commission varies from category  to category. Please contact us to know more at merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">9. What are the logistics charges? Can we charge the customer for shipping?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">The logistics charges are Rs. 45/- per 500gms (incremental on every 500gms by 45/-). Normally, Paytm doesn't charge the customer for shipping separately; however, you may include the shipping charges within the selling price. In case of low value products, we can specify shipping charges separately. </span></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">If you are selling products with a volumetric weight more than 10 kilos, we can ship these products by surface and will charge about Rs. 20/- per kilo.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>10. Can I upload the products on Paytm on my own? Can I do it once I'm registered?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">If a particular product already exists on Paytm then you can tag it on your own through the seller panel that has a search function. In case of new products, you need to submit a catalogue to Paytm and it will be uploaded by the Paytm catalogue team.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>11.  What are the image specifications for Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3">Once signed up you find all the 'Useful documents' in your seller panel to guide you further.</p>
<p class="p3"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">12. Can I ship my orders on my own through my own courier partners?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Yes, you can use your own logistics. However; Paytm has the widest range of pin code serviceability and a large number of trusted courier partners that will be there for your support. In case you use your own logistics, your products can’t be made live on COD (cash on delivery) and only prepaid orders will be allowed.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>13. Can I sell outside India through Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Currently Paytm is providing the facility to sell only in India.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>14. What are the Payment terms?</strong></p>
<p class="p2"><span class="s1">Paytm's payment cycle is 2 to 7 days, e.g. payments are made on every Friday or Monday for all the ‘delivered’ products till Thursday.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><strong>15. What is the number of days for accepting returns?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">We have a 15 days no questions asked return commitment with our customers.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>16. What is the return policy?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Returns could be in following cases:</span></p>

<ol class="ol2">
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">The customer isn't at his premises – In that case if after 3 trials also the customer is unavailable, the reverse logistics will be borne by Paytm.</span></li>
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">The customer returns the product without opening /change of mind/return to origin – In that case the merchant will not be charged and Paytm will bear the reverse logistics.</span></li>
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">The customer returns the product within 15 days since he didn't like it – In that case, if the product is correct and as per the specification on Paytm, reverse logistics will be borne by Paytm.</span></li>
	<li class="li2"><span class="s1">The customer returns a product since it is damaged/wrong/size mismatch etc. – In that case, the reverse logistics will be borne by the seller since the product was damaged/wrong.</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="p3"><strong><span class="s1">17. Who will be held responsible in case of damaged products delivered to the customer?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">If the damaged/wrong/ product is sent by the seller, the seller will be liable. However, if it got damaged during the transport, it will not be charged to the seller if proved. The discretion lies with the Paytm logistics team to decide.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>18. If I list my products on Paytm, will the customer know that s/he's is purchasing from me on Paytm?</strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">We give you the option for a brand name or merchant name to be displayed with the product. Hence, the customer will know from whom is s/he's buying the product.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">19. In how many days the product needs to be dispatched for delivery?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">The SLAs could be 6 days in case of the manufacturers. However, we encourage our sellers to dispatch their products as soon as possible. It is good for maintaining their reputation and to get repeat orders if the SLA is kept within at 1-2 days.</span></p>
<strong> 20. Can I cancel my subscription?</strong>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">Yes, you can choose to cancel your subscription any time at Paytm.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">21. </span>In case of any offers by Paytm, will I get the price quoted by me i.e irrespective of any cashback offers, discounts etc?</strong></p>
<p class="p2"><span class="s1">In such cases, we will clarify with you, sometimes the discounts offered is completely from our side but sometime we require the sellers to participate and reduce their margins for offer. In any case, you will be intimated before such deals and offers.</span></p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1"><span class="s1">There are many reasons why you should <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">sell at Paytm</a>. The best one - we are India's largest mCommerce platform and have 6 Crore customers to whom you can sell your products to. With our ongoing attractive promotions we're regularly boosting your sales. We spend on highly aggressive marketing across platforms and channels to bring more visibility to categories that we highlight. Our efforts include:</span></p>

<ul>
	<li class="p1"><span class="s1"><a href="https://paytm.com/blog/upto-100-on-home-kitchen-products-paytmkaro/" target="_blank">Front page newspaper advertisement in national newspapers</a>,</span></li>

	<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Push notifications &amp; sms to our customers.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="p1">Take the advantage and <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">grow your business</a> further in participating in <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm's</a> promotions. Our sales team reaches out to you for the same. Paytm is the most efficient way to do business with. You'll be amazed at what happens. Read here a success story from Basement Bazaar, where they got the best of #SellMoreWithPaytm :</p>

	<item>
		<title>Why to sell online - 5 Benefits of Paytm&#039;s Marketplace</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/why-to-sell-online-with-paytm-5-benefits-of-our-marketplace/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2015 12:36:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=115</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Do you want to increase your sales quicker, reduce your business operating costs and increase profit margins for your business? Then <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">selling online with Paytm</a> is the effective way for you.</div>
<div>

With the growing internet penetration and  millions online shoppers, who are searching <span style="color: #333333;">everyday the internet for products, you can’t avoid to be online. Online shopping is increasing year on year and is being seen as a convenient method to purchase products, where you can also buy at any time in the day.</span>

Additionally <a href="https://paytm.com/sellers/2015/05/22/what-you-get-when-you-sellmorewithpaytm/" target="_blank">Paytm supports your marketing</a> and sales techniques to give customs that extra reason to buy your products. So what are the key benefits that Paytm offers for your business?

<strong>Market reach</strong> - By being an online seller you are not restricting your potential customers, as they can view your products at any time of day from anywhere. Selling online allows you to reach customers outside of their towns and states and so you're able to generate a wider demand. Customers can find your products 24/7 on Paytm. You product visibility that you can gain with Paytm means that your business can encourage new customers at any time in the day. This means as a business, you are maximising your sales and profits. <strong>Over 8 crore customers have placed their trust in <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and shop online with us. We help you reach millions of users.</strong>

<strong>Competition</strong><span style="color: #333333;"> - If you're not online yet, you're not competing within</span><span style="color: #333333;"> this growing sales channel. Other sellers online are capturing customers that could be already yours.</span><span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>

<strong>Customer service</strong><span style="color: #333333;"> -  We give our sellers a dedicated support. Just contact us at <span style="text-decoration: underline;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span>! We'd love to hear from you.</span>
<div class="adL">

<strong>Data</strong> -<strong> </strong>By tracking what your customers have ordered, viewed, etc. your online sales system can offer a better sales experience. With the <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Paytm Seller Dashboard</a> your can review your current stock, analyze your products which may have a better ROI and avoid overbooking. That helps you to make the most effective use of your current product inventory and optimize your stock. The Paytm Seller Dashboard helps merchants to keep track of all orders and to improve your online sales!

<strong>Save time/money</strong>: The costs for <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">setting up your Paytm account</a> are zero. Our Merchant Helpdesk supports you with the initial set up that is simple and saves you time. As everything is well settled, you don't need to do anything, other then to setup and upload the catalog. Paytm provides you a whole automated online system that not only helps you in uploading your catalog, but also makes the process of customers ordering and making payments smooth for your business. This will give you more time to review your product performances, determine new products you want to sell, special offers you want to launch and to track how successful your sales are.

Paytm helps you to expand your business faster than that it is normally possible within an offline business situation.
<p dir="ltr"><strong>How to make most out of your Paytm marketplace:</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>Sign-up <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">now</a></li>
	<li>Be open to experiment with discounts and participate in our offer schemes and sales promotions</li>
	<li>Learn everything that you want to know about selling online with Paytm</li>
	<li>Use your Paytm Seller Dashboard to gain knowledge of your business performance, how customers are responding to your products.</li>
	<li>Encourage customer feedback on your products</li>
</ul>
Become part of the Paytm family! Join 40,000 sellers!

</div>

	<item>
		<title>Ways to improve your inventory management</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=492</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=330</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400">Inventory management is an essential activity involved in any business and requires for availability of sufficient amount of products in optimal quantities. So, make efforts to maintain sufficient and ample stock at all times as this would help in efficient control over inventory management and in turn reap great returns. Maintaining an ideal inventory management system is also a pivotal tool to drive your sales and achieve great success in eCommerce.You can target good sales if you manage your product inventory efficiently.To boost sales and to prevent situations like ‘Out of stock’ and products getting completely ‘Sold Out’ follow below measures.</span>

<b><b>A) Averting Low stock situations :</b></b>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Make sure that you have sufficient inventory.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Avert procurement delay from suppliers. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Plan accordingly for a promotional activity.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Take care of seasonal fluctuations and requirement demand.</span></li>
</ol>
<strong>B) Factors for Managing inventory:</strong>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ability to forecast future sales accurately: For sales forecast, take care of the  average past sales, expected future sales growth and sales fluctuations like promotional activities and seasonal variations.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ordering  concepts: Sufficient stock should be maintained keeping procurement delays and sudden high demand in mind. Keep a track on number of days the inventory will last  so new and the right quantity of orders could be placed timely.</span></li>
</ol>
<b>C) Stock Keeping Unit(SKU) Update:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Always update SKU whenever new stock is added or a product’s price changes. You can update inventory in two following ways:</span>

<b>i) Single SKU update</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Single SKU update is used when you change details of the catalog for only one single product.  In Catalog, you will select single product and update for its change in price, MRP, quantity or any other field if any.</span>

<b>ii) Bulk SKU update</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> : Bulk update is used to update SKU for multiple products in a single go. To execute this, select ALL Tab-Product Details and then select the products for which you need to update the SKU and download the CSV file of the selected products. Open the downloaded file, make necessary changes in the fields, save as a CSV file and upload this new file of catalog updation.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400">Maintaining enough stock  and regular catalog update is essential from time to time for effectively managing an inventory. This will also surely attract customers to come,browse and purchase your products. In case, if you come across any issue or need any assistance while uploading, updating CSV file or while managing your inventory then we are just a click away at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> .</span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Ship Fast: Mantra to woo your online customers</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=494</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=338</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400">Modern buyers acknowledge fast delivery and love to receive booked products in the minimum time. These online booked orders normally take 2-3 days to reach customers. However, at times due to several factors, the shipping is delayed and the order fails to reach on-time at its destination. Let’s say a buyer who made an online purchase received his order the very next day will surely show up for repeat purchases in future because of his recent satisfactory experience of fast and timely shipping.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400">All consumers love to receive products in minimum time once they book their  and now, a  large number of people who shop online look forward to urgent delivery and fast shipping. For consumers, the early you deliver, the more closer you bring them to a great shopping experience helping build customer confidence as the time gap between offline and online buying experience gets greatly reduced.</span>

<b>Tips for fast shipping :</b>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400">Shipping commitment<span style="font-weight: 400">: Always adhere to timely and quick shipping, keep watch on inventory  so there’s enough stock and avail services from trustworthy and reputed logistic partner to ship the order.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Plan for enough stock in advance before participating in a promotion so you do not run out of stock leaving buyers disappointed.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400">Give details for tracking the order<b>:</b><span style="font-weight: 400">This will help in customer satisfaction and will enhance customer experience.</span></li>
</ol>
<b>Benefits of  fast shipping:</b>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Helps in preventing ‘Cancel Order’ due to unsatisfactory/late delivery</b><span style="font-weight: 400">:Buyers often cancel orders when they do not receive a product on time. Fast and timely shipping would help bring such 'cancel order/ purchase'  cases down.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Commitment- Assure Speedy Delivery</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Buyers would love to shop again and again if they get the products on time and this will in turn help increase your sales and earn more from it.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Pool of trusted buyers</b><span style="font-weight: 400">:You will win trust of buyers and will see an increase in your customer pool if you sell with commitment and offer fast shipment. This in turn will have a positive impact on your business and increase your sales profit.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>High prestige and reputation</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Delivering in assured time would help you win high prestige and great reputation amongst the pool of trusted customers that you have and people would love to buy again from you for the promise and commitment you offer them.</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Know more about Paytm&#039;s promotions</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/know-more-about-paytms-promotions/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2015 08:57:58 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=146</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/06/promotions_blog.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="352" />

As customers love to save money, they look out for Paytm's promotions which are an incentive for them to make a buying decision sooner rather later or to choose one product or seller over another.

Our Seller Team invites you as sellers on a regular basis to different promotions that we're running. Every offer has indirect and/or direct benefits for you. When you enroll for them, your shortlisted products will be displayed under the promotional category and get labelled with the relevant offers (cashback or discount). Further Paytm runs special marketing campaigns around each promotion across media (print + online) which attracts customers to buy and you get the chance to sell more.

Here's how it works for you:
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>1. How can I participate?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1">If you are shortlisted for any upcoming campaign, you will receive an invitation e-mail from your<b> Seller Management Team</b> (<a class="Xx" href="mailto:sellmore@paytm.com" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer">sellmore@paytm.com</a>) asking your participation. You will need to share a list of products that you wish to include in the campaign. If you match the requirements of the campaign, you will be eligible to participate.</p>
<p class="p1"><!--more--></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>2.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>How will the campaign be beneficial for me?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Through the campaign, your products will receive better visibility on Paytm's marketplace website and app. Your shortlisted products will appear labeled with the relevant offer, which will attract more customers and gives you the opportunity to sell more with Paytm.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>3. How many products can I list for the campaign?</b></span></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s1">There is no upper limit on the number of products that you can participate with. You will need to share a list of products which will be screened by the Paytm team. After screening, your products found eligible will be considered for the campaign. </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>4. How will I come to know about the products that are shortlisted for the campaign?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">After you have shared the list of products with your Seller Management Team, you will receive an e-mail stating that <b>“all your products have been shortlisted”</b> OR<b> “your products have been partially shortlisted” </b>OR<b> “your products have not been shortlisted”</b>. You can get further details by writing to your Seller Management Team (<a href="mailto:sellmore@paytm.com"><span class="s2">sellmore@paytm.com</span></a>). </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>5. In what format will I share my list of products?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">You will need to fill your product details in a template that you will receive along with the invitation e-mail.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>6. How much discount will I need to give on my products?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Based on the campaign, you will receive needful details along with our participation invitation e-mail which is clearly stating the discounts and other incentives that you will need to give on your products.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b>7. What will be the structure of commissions and logistics?</b></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Standard charges for commissions and logistics will apply. Incase of any changes in the same, the detailed structure will be provided in our invitation e-mail.</span></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paytm ties up with online loan provider Capital Float</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-ties-up-with-online-loan-provider-capital-float/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2015 12:50:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=242</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="https://paytm.com/">Paytm</a> partners with Capital Float to offer you collateral free loans! This is an opportunity for our <a href="http://seller.paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm sellers</a> to give you the best financial solutions.

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/07/capital-float_2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="456" />

The loan powered by <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.capitalfloat.com/" target="_blank">Capital Float</a> helps you to grow your business as you’ll be able to:
<ul>
	<li>Buy more stock to increase sales</li>
	<li>Launch new brands, categories &amp; products in a big way</li>
	<li>Get cash discounts from suppliers by paying up-front</li>
</ul>
Your benefits:
<ul>
	<li>Collateral free loans based on Paytm sales</li>
	<li>Seamless UX delivered via a completely online application process taking no more than 9 min to complete</li>
	<li>Minimal documents required</li>
	<li>Industry leading TAT of 3-7 days for loan disbursement</li>
</ul>
Through this partnership we strive to empower sellers with working capital finance to assist you run your business on Paytm's marketplace with ease.

Apply for your loan <strong><a href="https://safe.capitalfloat.com/cf/default/register" target="_blank">now</a></strong> and receive funds in a week’s time.

Times of India covered the news. Read it <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/Paytm-ties-up-with-online-loan-provider/articleshow/48027110.cms" target="_blank">here</a>.

		<title>Google Hangout for Seller Training</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/google-hangout-for-seller-training/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2015 07:29:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=176</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Our Google Hangouts are help-outs for you! <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm's</a> Seller Training team provides now Live Google Hangouts for you. A trainer will take you through a specific topic and answer all your questions around your Paytm seller panel. All trainings are held online and are free.

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/06/Google-hangout_post-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" />

You just need an internet connection, a laptop or desktop and headphones or speakers to start.

<strong># How to Join</strong>

1. Login to your Gmail account.

2. Then simply click on the links below to join the event on your preferred date.  Kindly join us at least 5 min before it starts.

<strong># Topics</strong>
<ol>
	<li>How to list your products</li>
	<li>How to manage your orders</li>
	<li>Returns and policies</li>
	<li>Payments and policies</li>
	<li>Question and answer session for query resolution</li>
</ol>
Please join us on the links below at your preferred date:

<strong># Sessions</strong>

		<title>Paytm spending aggressively on seller empowerment with new platform GoBig</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-spending-aggressively-on-seller-empowerment-with-new-platform-gobig/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2015 09:52:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=224</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[With our commitment towards sellers in the country, we've taken another big step to empower SMEs. Digitalization helps SMEs to thrive and Paytm invests in this development by setting up <a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank">GoBig</a> -  a platform that provides services to support sellers go online and grow their business. GoBig is for businesses of all sizes and an opportunity for SMEs to level the playing field and compete online. It's a powerful platform for sellers that supports them to lead this new wave of growth.

Read the Economic Times <a href="http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-07-08/news/64212130_1_lakh-crore-paytm-sellers" target="_blank">coverage</a>:<a href="http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-07-08/news/64212130_1_lakh-crore-paytm-sellers" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/07/Econoic-times_new-article.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="1355" /></a>

Are you a part of Paytm's seller family? Then check out <a href="http://gobig.paytm.com/" target="_blank">GoBig</a> and let us know your feedback. Not a seller yet? Sign up <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">now</a>.

		<title>Google Hangouts for Paytm Non-LMD sellers</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/google-hangouts-for-paytm-non-lmd-sellers/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2015 10:02:33 +0000</pubDate>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We're excited to announce new Google Hangouts specifically for our Paytm non-LMD sellers to help them understand better functioning of Seller Panel. These sessions will include all operations related with non-LMD sellers who execute orders using their own logistics.You can attend these Google Hangout sessions from anywhere and just need an internet connection, a laptop/desktop/Smartphone, headphones or speakers to join in.

<strong># How to Join</strong>
<ol>
	<li>Login to your Gmail account.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
	<li>Click on the links below to join the event on your preferred date.  Kindly join us at least 5 min before it starts.</li>
</ol>
<strong># Topics</strong>

How to process non-LMD orders

Order-to-ship SLAs for non-LMD orders

Updates in the Seller Panel

Question-and-answer session on non-LMD order processing

<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Please join us on the links below at your preferred date:</strong></span>

		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-invests-in-delivery-reach-to-connect-merchants-to-consumers-across-india/</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Paytm invests Rs. 100 Cr in a strong cloud network through regional courier companies, as well as India post, to close one of the biggest e-commerce barriers and connect merchants with a large network of courier partners. Currently <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> serves 39,000 pin codes across the country which sellers can leverage to grow their businesses. A high Pan-India delivery performance is a key driver for the success of <a href="https://sellon.paytm.com/" target="_blank">online sellers</a>' businesses. We have a commitment to bring sellers and the delivery sector together to provide workable solutions. Learn more about our plans from the <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/Paytm-to-invest-Rs-100cr-in-cloud-to-expand-reach/articleshow/47808810.cms" target="_blank">coverage</a> in Times of India:

		<title>Paytm is the Title Sponsor for all India Cricket till 2019!</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-is-the-title-sponsor-for-all-india-cricket-till-2019/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Aug 2015 06:46:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=298</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We are very happy to inform you that <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is the <strong>Title Sponsor for all <a href="http://www.bcci.tv/" target="_blank">BCCI</a> cricket in India for the next 4 years!</strong>

As a growing brand that has big plans for a billion strong Indians, there is no better platform than cricket in India. We believe that this association will go a long way towards reinforcing our commitment as a serious long term player, enhancing our brand stature &amp; <strong><em>connecting you with millions of customers.</em></strong>

We believe this is just the beginning &amp; we are delighted to have you as part of the growing Paytm family.

Our CEO, <a href="https://twitter.com/vijayshekhar">Vijay Shekhar Sharma</a>, explains our new association in interviews with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hXL3QMVVTGQ&amp;feature=youtu.be">Bloomberg TV</a> and <a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/et-now/daily/paytm-bags-bcci-title-sponsorship-rights/videoshow/48283632.cms">ET NOW</a>. Watch them now to get the details!

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/BCCI.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" />

	<item>
		<title>Introducing Do-It-Yourself Catalog Management on Paytm&#039;s Seller Panel</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/introducing-do-it-yourself-catalog-management-on-paytms-seller-panel/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 19 Aug 2015 07:03:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=305</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Catalog_mgmt.jpg"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Catalog_mgmt.jpg" alt="" width="591" height="241" /></a>

Managing any of your products online is very crucial as this helps you to <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">sell more</a> on Paytm.  The simple and essential step by step feature of managing your catalog is important as it empowers you to manage your product catalogue on your own.

Today, we're happy to introduce Paytm's Do-It-Yourself (<strong>DYI</strong>) process on our <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Seller Panel</a> for you. The Catalog DIY feature allows you to:
<ul>
	<li>Add/tag a product, which already exists in <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm Marketplace</a>, to your own catalog.</li>
	<li>Add a new size to an apparel or footwear that you have already listed in your own catalog.</li>
	<li>Create and add a new product that is not listed in Paytm Marketplace to your own catalog.</li>
</ul>
Learn how to do it:

<strong># Adding a new variant to an existing group of products in your own catalog.</strong>

This feature helps you to simply add a new variant to a product that already exists in your catalog.

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog1.jpg"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog1.jpg" alt="" width="591" height="341" /></a>

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog1.jpg">
</a><strong># Add existing product</strong>

Before you add a complete new product to your catalog, search if the product already exist to make the process easier for you. Here you've the option to 'search' on Paytm's entire catalog and the option to add the same as a new product to your own catalog.

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog-2.jpg" alt="" width="591" height="551" /></a>

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/catalog-2.jpg">
</a><strong># Create new products</strong>

We made it easy for you to add a completely new product, which is not yet sold on Paytm, to your own catalog in a few steps.

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/CATALOG-3.jpg" alt="" width="591" height="863" />

You've to keep in mind that for every new addition there are catalog approval stages done from our team to maintain correct information for our customers. To learn more about the whole process <a href="http://seller.paytm.com/" target="_blank">login</a> to our Paytm Seller Panel and check the learning manual in our <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Seller Training Centre</a>.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paytm &amp; InMobi partner to create the largest discovery &amp; mobile shopping platform in India</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/paytm-inmobi-partner-to-create-the-largest-discovery-mobile-shopping-platform-in-india/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 17 Aug 2015 07:39:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=346</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1"><span class="s1">We’re excited to tie up with InMobi, the <a href="http://www.inmobi.com/en/" target="_blank">world’s most powerful mobile advertising platform</a>, in a multi level partnership with an aspiration to turbo charge the <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">mobile commerce</a> ecosystem. </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Seeing Paytm grow to 100 million users blows our mind and yet, it’s only the beginning. Our aspirations are much bigger. Joining hands with <a href="http://www.inmobi.com/en/" target="_blank">InMobi</a> combines the power of <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">m-commerce</a> with d-commerce (discovery commerce) in a big way.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">So what’s (in it) new for you, you ask?</span></p>
<p class="p1"><strong><span class="s1">Unmatched user reach for Paytm sellers</span></strong></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">As sellers on our Paytm marketplace you will now have reach to an extended universe of 120 million mobile internet users on InMobi’s Miip d-commerce platform. While earlier you were able to sell only to our Paytm universe, you can now increase your business manifold by reaching out to the entire mobile internet community in India. Our partnership will power billions of <a href="http://www.inmobi.com/en/" target="_blank">d-commerce</a> sessions, thus exponentially increasing the reach of the combined platform. We know that access to a wide market and a user-friendly <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">payment solution</a> are the two most critical elements for you to increase your business. Our association with InMobi will provide exactly this solution to you.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><strong><span class="s1">Buy buttons powered by Paytm Wallet on Miip platform </span></strong></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Our Paytm Wallet will enable seamless checkouts on the <a href="http://www.inmobi.com/en/" target="_blank">Miip</a> zone in more than thousands of apps. It ensures that sellers have higher sales conversions as the Paytm Wallet (with over 100 million users) is optimized to ensure minimum payment failures and provide higher convenience for <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">mobile payments</a>.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><strong><span class="s1">Digital store on Paytm App</span></strong></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Our app users get access to latest apps &amp; games on their smartphones through the <a href="https://paytm.com/mobile" target="_blank">Paytm App</a> powered by InMobi’s <a href="http://www.inmobi.com/en/" target="_blank">Miip platform</a>. All the apps and games you’ll see on the store are free to install and can be easily downloaded from Google Play or the Apple App Store. This digital store will also offer you in the future music and video content directly from the <a href="https://paytm.com/mobile" target="_blank">Paytm App</a>.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">How cool is that?!</span></p>
<p class="p1">Get more details of the <a href="http://telecom.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/paytm-ties-up-with-inmobi/48493432" target="_blank">news</a> on Economic Times.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Master the Art of Selling with Paytm’s September Google Hangouts</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/master-the-art-of-selling-with-paytms-september-google-hangouts/</link>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We're at Paytm are here to help you grow your business and that's why we continue to bring you our Google Hangout training! The upcoming new Google Hangout training sessions will help you to improve your business and sell more with <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a>. This time we'll offer you topic-specific sessions and feature LMD (short for Last Mile Delivery) and Non-LMD merchants. As LMD sellers or Non -MD <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">sellers</a> you can plan better which particular topic to attend.

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Google-hangout_blogpost_1-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="529" />

<strong># How to Join</strong>
<ol>
	<li>Login to your Gmail account.</li>
	<li>Then simply click on the links below to join the event on your preferred date.  Kindly join us at least 5 min before it starts.</li>
</ol>
<strong># Topics  </strong>
<ul>
	<li>Getting Started</li>
	<li>Catalog</li>
	<li>Dashboard</li>
	<li>Announcements</li>
	<li>Settings</li>
	<li>Orders</li>
	<li>Returns</li>
	<li> Payments</li>
</ul>

		<pubDate>Fri, 18 Sep 2015 14:07:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=377</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[&nbsp;

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-1-blog-post.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-449 alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-1-blog-post.jpg" alt="seller-story-1-blog-post" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<b>Read how Sunil Dhingra became the largest online seller of Car and Bike Accessories with his venture </b><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25251&amp;mn=Jazzmyride"><b>JazzMyRide</b></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">ECommerce is booming and more and more consumers spend their money online. Going online can bring significant benefits for entrepreneurs in growing a business, and is an efficient mechanism for reaching a wider audience and improving sales. Meet in our success stories that we will be sharing with you normal people who built thriving online businesses on </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn from our dynamic sellers that everyone can build successful online stores that allow you to earn a good living and live your passions.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Building an online business gives anyone an incredible business opportunity! What we love about our sellers messages is that they’re not promising overnight riches. They’re saying that regular folks can successfully sell online.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sunil Dhingra is one of our success stories. He runs </span><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25251&amp;mn=Jazzmyride"><span style="font-weight: 400;">JazzMyRide</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and shares his insights and advice for would-be online sellers.</span>

<b>You're one of top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">At JazzMyRide, we sell Car &amp; Bike Accessories &amp; Spare Parts. We had started with a set of 20-30 very basic accessories like perfume, car mobile holder, etc. However, we did grow fast and today we have got an assortment of more than 70,000 products! We add approximately 3000 new products every week to our catalogue.</span>

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25251&amp;mn=Jazzmyride" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story_collage-2_blog-post_18-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="500" /></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The biggest positive transition has been to be able to sell spare parts like shockers, clutch plates, brake pads, air filters, etc completely online and a lot of them through Paytm itself.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Car &amp; Bike is quite a unique and niche category to be sold online in India. Though, there is a great demand for this category but the supply chain is pretty unorganised in the offline market as well. Therefore, we chose the online model to streamline the supply chain and to solve the problem of availability, duplicacy &amp; fair pricing.</span>

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25251&amp;mn=Jazzmyride" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story_collage-1_18-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We never compromise on the quality of our products. We believe that offering a superior shopping experience to our customers will encourage them to return. We’re go over the top to ensure every customer is happy with their purchase. We inspect every product received from our suppliers &amp; partners to ensure that it is ourselves who find any defects, rather than our customers. We make sure to ship in time and that all products are of outstanding quality.</span>

<b>What got you into doing your own business?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I had made my first e-commerce sale 15 years back when I was in school. At that moment itself, I got hooked on to selling online. Though, it has taken a wait of 15 years to witness the e-commerce boom and I am full on trying to ride on the same.</span>

<b>How did you get into selling online and came to know about Paytm?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The e-commerce selling formally started in 2011. Having worked with all the leading e-commerce marketplaces as a seller, we liked the fresh approach that Paytm brought into this ecosystem. We associated for the launch of auto accessories category with Paytm and since then it has been a phenomenal run. </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm’s seller systems</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> had been equally commendable like consumer facing systems.</span>

<b>What were your first challenges of selling online?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To organise an unorganised category’s supply chain is a big challenge in itself. Added to it the evolving ecommerce processes and systems, building a passionate team, and doing all this in a bootstrapped yet profitable manner has been quite an exciting &amp; challenging journey.</span>

<b>What is your typical day like as an online seller?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now having a team of 80 people, my majority of the time goes into strategic planning, financial and human resource management. One of our unique core values is automation which helps us automate our regular business flow and allow us to keep inventing something new to stay ahead of the curve.</span>

<b>If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do to increase their online sales, what would it be?</b>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Invest in rock-solid systems that help you manage your operations efficiently. You need systems that help you to connect with shipping suppliers and automate your daily work. Doing so will give your business room to grow. Through the use of an online system, you can link together every aspect of your business including point of sale, shipping and accounting. The right kind of eCommerce system will help you make your company’s relationship with a drop shipper run much smoother (for example preventing inventory errors, out-of-stock issues etc.). A reliable system provides you with accurate data and inventory that helps create good shopping experience for your customers too.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Though slowly but keep adding a strong and passionate team. Most of the sellers take e-commerce selling like selling through a shop, assuming they can do it mostly on their own. But since e-commerce sale has much larger scalability scope and opportunities to go big, if you do not hire the right team you will quickly hit upon a roadblock to scale ahead.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Be very careful about your profitability analysis, legal and taxation compliances. Do not take it as a short-term pocket money business. There is no shortcut to success - proper work with suppliers that are certified to sell products and selling only original parts is the key.</span></li>
</ol>
<b>What's your advice for new sellers coming online?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t blindly join the e-commerce bandwagon as it sounds too attractive at the moment. Before you take the plunge, do your thorough homework of understanding what problem you are going to solve and how you are going to position yourself uniquely in the market.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We could anticipate the </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login"><span style="font-weight: 400;">e-commerce</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> boom coming and started invested in back-end technologies and supply chain. Luckily, we also picked the right category that has all the ingredients to become a really big category in the coming years ahead.</span>

<a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> today!

Stay in touch with us to get to know more success stories, just follow us on our Facebook pages <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Paytm-Sellers-936347589760198/timeline/?ref=bookmarks" target="_blank">Paytm Sellers</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/paytm" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and on <a href="https://twitter.com/paytm" target="_blank">Twitter</a>! We'd love to hear from you.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The sweet sound of success! Selling electronics profitably online</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/the-sweet-sound-of-success-selling-electronics-profitably-online/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Sep 2015 10:31:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=398</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-3-blog-post.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-454 alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-3-blog-post.jpg" alt="seller-story-3-blog-post" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;">As entrepreneurs look to get new businesses up and running quickly, many are heading straight online. When you take the plunge as an <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">e-commerce entrepreneur</a>, there’s a world of opportunity out there. Running an online business can be one of the most rewarding career paths you can choose.</span>

Get several tips from our new generation of e-commerce success stories.

<b>Meet Sachin from <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25154&amp;mn=Happy%20Hours&amp;q=&amp;category=8027&amp;from=organic&amp;sort_price=1" target="_blank">Happy Hours</a> - an unstoppable online seller! Find out more about his online business.</b>

<b>You're one of the top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them.</b>

Thanks! Our main category has always been electronics. We sell a variety of products from trimers to style kits for young generations; home appliances to kitchen appliances to everything in the house. It feels like we are becoming a part of many families through selling our electronics, home &amp; kitchen appliances &amp; baby category products online.

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25154&amp;mn=Happy%20Hours&amp;q=&amp;category=8027&amp;from=organic&amp;sort_price=1" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-3_blog-post_22-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="648" /></a>

<b>What got you into doing your own business?</b>

A strong will to achieve something bigger. And I always wanted to build an organization which is based on a modern and innovative distribution system. Selling on an <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">online marketplace</a> helps maximise your distribution as it connects sellers to many more customers. I also love the working flexibility by selling online and can make my own 9 to 5 schedule.

<b>How did you get into <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">selling online</a> and came to know about Paytm?</b>

Limitless boundaries is my  answer, I guess. You don’t need to work on old Brick &amp; Mortar based model, having a physical store where I need to relay of customers to walk in. Selling online opened our business up to Pan India. I still remember our initial days when we have had a 100 product catalogue, were adding an average sales of 5-10 products in day. That’s how we started. It gradually increased day by day and was incredible to see. By today, we have an operational capacity of fulfilling 1000 orders per day with a catalogue size of more than 50 brands and 2000+ products. That’s a fantastic growth.

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=25154&amp;mn=Happy%20Hours&amp;q=&amp;category=8027&amp;from=organic&amp;sort_price=1" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-3_collage_22-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We are a big fan of <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> since its launch as a company. Paytm has itself developed from initially doing online recharges to a full-flatted marketplace and a big online players in the “<a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Online Marketplaces</a>” in India. It’s a change, and how can we resist to be a part of this great change and development.</span>

<b>What were your first challenges of selling online?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For us it was a long journey. We have started our online business, when there was no simplified procedure or no marketplaces at all. From the onboarding of products, doing marketing and then timely delivery every segment has its own challenges. Thanks to the new marketplaces that ease our selling procedures and gives us a chance to focus on products and delivery only. It takes away a lot of your headache when you work with the infrastructure of a marketplace and you can focus on what you are good in - selling. </span>

<b>What is your typical day like as Paytm seller?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Being an online business, you have typical days. Orders are coming in and you have to ship your products. That is our routine. We are working every day hard to deliver the best quality to our customers in time so that they return back with business.</span>

<img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/seller-story-3-blog-post-end.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" />

<b>If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do to increase their online sales, what would it be?</b>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t JUST COPY others. Before selling any product, analyze the demand of customers and then build your catalogue yourself. Don’t think that only having cheap price is the way to be on top in this industry, rather focus on product based strategy.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Make your product catalogue very dynamic, keep changing and update your product line from time to time to stay attractive for your buyers.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Analyze your returns, identify the reason for returns and improve it with a better and practical plan. Customer satisfaction is the ultimate goal, without customers there is no business.</span></li>
</ul>
<b>What's your advice for new sellers coming online?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Think Innovative, think big and be dynamic! Treat your product catalogue as an individual, and multiply your products with quality to make your catalogue a perfect bestseller in your industry. Don’t be only profit centric in the early days, try to build a long term relationship with your customers. Success does not come overnight. You have to work for it, work for your customers. Give it time and dedication and you will succeed. <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Start selling now.</a></span>

<a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> today!

Stay in touch with us to get to know more success stories, just follow us on our Facebook pages <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Paytm-Sellers-936347589760198/timeline/?ref=bookmarks" target="_blank">Paytm Sellers</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/paytm" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and on <a href="https://twitter.com/paytm" target="_blank">Twitter</a>! We'd love to hear from you.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Meet online seller Ehealthmart and know the incredible power of selling online</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/meet-online-seller-ehealthmart-and-know-the-incredible-power-of-selling-online/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Sep 2015 05:37:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=393</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-2-blog-post.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-452 alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/seller-story-2-blog-post.jpg" alt="seller-story-2-blog-post" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;">We love sharing business success stories, especially when they are about ordinary people who achieve extraordinary internet business success.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">It has been said that the internet levels the playing field for everyone. These types of success stories give anyone a chance to anyone, irrespective of age, education, or location to become successful in </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login"><span style="font-weight: 400;">selling online</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Here is one more online success story - get to know how this seller takes advantage of the Paytm platform and outlines his experiences:</span>

<b>Read how Rishabh Jain has become one of the most successful online seller of our Health and Wellness Category with his venture <a href="https://paytm.com/@ehealthmart" target="_blank">Ehealthmart</a>.</b>

<strong>You're one of top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them. </strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We are Delhi based and everyday have to ship products to thousands of our on online customers. Our products range is health, wellness , nutrition and baby care products.</span>

<a href="https://paytm.com/@ehealthmart" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-2_blog-post_2_21-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="648" /></a>

<strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">What got you into doing your own business?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We are a decade old company dealing in Pharmaceutical, Healthcare &amp; Nutrition Products. As we were a Delhi based company and realized that in future eCommerce is going to be the next face of shopping in the world, so we empowered ourselves to reach Pan India and serve to all class of customers. Therefore we forayed into e-commerce business. It was a steady learning by doing and still is.</span>

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-2_collage_21-9-15.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-2_collage_21-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">How did you get into selling online and came to know about Paytm?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">2014 was a transformation phase for both eCommerce and mCommerce in India, and we were looking to venture into m-commerce business. <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is the leader in </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login"><span style="font-weight: 400;">mCommerce</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> business sector, the moment we heard about it, we signed up and and began selling merchandise on it.</span>

<strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;">What were your first challenges of selling online?</span></strong>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Educated Manpower: When you start to operate your new online business in the beginning you will maybe wear every hat yourself. Finally, when you will hit your breaking point, where, in order to remain competitive and prosper, you'll need to welcome a helping hand aboard your business. But before bringing just anyone on board, you need to understand your requirements and analyze where exactly you need help. Once you've completed your behind-the-scenes evaluation, make it a point to hire trained staff. It might take some time to find the right people, but it’s worth the effort.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Inventory &amp; Invoicing Software: You want to know your business’s financial position at all times, but let’s admit it nobody wants to worry about it all the time. There are softwares online for small businesses to manage the basic inventory and accounting tasks. They help you with inventory and invoicing, quickly and accurately every time a customer makes a purchase from you.  This helps you to increase your financial management and productivity.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Payments &amp; Return Management: Handling the backoffice of your business can be complex. But once you do it right it will give you great growth opportunities. Define what payment options do you plan to offer your customers - credit cards, debit cards etc. Make sure to learn about the options and how Paytm can help you to integrate them seamlessly. Accepting payments is Paytm’s strength. Further give your customers service after they purchased products from you. Make your return policies easy to understand, and have quick and simple return process in place. These are very important for people buying online. Paytm helps you to handle returns with options to automate returns or manually approve them.</span></span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Catalog Management: Initially learning catalog management was bit complex for us. Expect it to take a little longer. I cannot stress the importance of learning this point. Your catalog is the face of your online business. Customers tend to look at the professionalism and uniformity of the information to judge your trustworthiness as a seller. Hence, display all relevant information correctly - fill up exact data including pricing, product specification, size and weight when required, warranties, licenses etc. Include attractive pictures of your products. Keep the catalog back-end handy, because this information tends to change often. With Paytm’s seller platform you have ready-made templates and online tools especially designed to help you create and maintain a product catalog for your online business. It helps you to quickly broadcast your products, make easily price changes, and introduce new products to your customers.</span></li>
</ul>
<strong>What is your typical day like as an online seller? </strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The various selling tools and tabs available on online selling portals makes a seller’s task easier, moreover the support staff is always great to help when we face any issue and help us carry our everyday operations smoothly. Of Course, we have to be at our toes throughout the day, but that the best part of this industry that it keeps you involved and updated about new challenges, growth &amp; learning. </span>

<strong>If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do  to increase their online sales, what would it be?</strong>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hire trained manpower. As stated earlier it is important to have qualified hands to support you in your day-to-day business. Take care of this point early when you start growing your online business. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Go for finance options: eCommerce businesses offer hassle-free finance options which help you scale your business. The loans provided make it possible for you to buy more stocks and launch new products to increase your sales.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow ethics &amp; discipline for the business: It’s important to be ethically correct and especially sell only original products as it allows you to </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">build a trusted reputation, foster repeat business and higher sales over time, develop a loyal customer base and minimise complaints about your business.</span></li>
</ul>
<strong>What's your advice for new sellers coming online? </strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As now, <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">e-commerce</a> has evolved into various models therefore there is enough business opportunity for all of us. Selling at multiple marketplaces is always lucrative, but new sellers should understand the target audience as a whole and the products which you want to target should be accordingly placed in the best suited marketplace. Also as a starter one should be very disciplined and should cope up with all the T&amp;Cs of the concerned marketplace for a hassle free journey.</span>

<a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> today!

Stay in touch with us to get to know more success stories, just follow us on our Facebook pages <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Paytm-Sellers-936347589760198/timeline/?ref=bookmarks" target="_blank">Paytm Sellers</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/paytm" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and on <a href="https://twitter.com/paytm" target="_blank">Twitter</a>! We'd love to hear from you.]]></content:encoded>
