	<item>
		<title>Meet KARAN MAHEDNRU - The passionate online Pet Supplies seller</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/meet-karan-mahednru-the-passionate-online-pet-supplies-seller/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2015 09:47:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=414</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-story-4_-blog-post_8-10-15.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-458 alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-story-4_-blog-post_8-10-15.jpg" alt="Seller-story-4_-blog-post_8-10-15" width="659" height="298" /></a>

Many small business owners are utilising the <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">online marketplace</a> to boost profits. Selling products through online marketplaces has become increasingly popular with <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">entrepreneurs</a> because of the low costs, flexibility and the feeling of being in control of your own business.

We’re happy to share another success story our <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Paytm sellers</a> - Karan Mahednru, the successful <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">online seller</a> who is excited to share his experience of running his business of Pet Supplies on Paytm’s marketplace.

Karan Mahendru, a pet enthusiast knows the significance of healthy and nutritious diet for your pets. He aims to provide enriched Pet supplies, pet accessories and collars chew bones and much more to animal lovers who shop online. Read about his experience of setting up a business online:

<strong>You're one of top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them.</strong>

We at ‘<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search?merchant=45411&amp;mn=THE%20PET%20POINT" target="_blank">The Pet Point</a>’ deal in pet supplies. We provide all basic necessities for pets ranging from food, to grooming to hygiene to online buyers customers. Starting from the basic necessity - the pet food to pet accessories, pet clothing and even pet health supplements and everything else which can help both the pet and the pet parent is readily available with us.

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=45411&amp;mn=THE%20PET%20POINT" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-4_webpage-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="648" /></a>

<strong>What got you into doing your own business?</strong>

I come from a family where everyone adores and is a pet lover. It was natural and easy to relate to this profession as I grew up in such an environment and since my childhood knew all basics about raising a pet - this learning immensely helped me relate to this business. I exactly knew all the hows, whens, whats and whys of pet supplies business. We right now are taking care of all the spheres in this business and provide both goods and services a pet parent needs for their pets.

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=45411&amp;mn=THE%20PET%20POINT" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-4_-products-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<strong>How did you get into selling online and came to know about Paytm?</strong>

Selling online was an important way to take our business onto a bigger platform that would help us meet today's competition and expectations. We started on with all other major marketplaces but when we were introduced to Paytm, the entire business routine changed for us. Now we are working with only three marketplaces and our major chunk of business comes from Paytm. We were infact one of the first sellers to get on board with Paytm when our category ‘Pet Supplies’ was launched. From about 2-3 orders a day, we have reached the limit where we receive around 150 orders in a day. This massive and unexpected growth has been possible through getting onboard on Paytm.

<strong>What were your first challenges of selling online?</strong>

Selling online was and is a different ball game altogether. Initial challenges included managing and updating catalog, packaging products and shipping orders. I must mention here that <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Paytm</a> is the only platform which has taken great care of these three major work challenges of the online business. From helping us to setting up our catalog to providing excellent packaging material to taking care of the shipping part, we never found it difficult to do business with Paytm.

<strong>What is your typical day like as an online seller?</strong>

A typical day starts with processing orders, manifesting them and getting them packed. Then comes making reports for returns and taking care of inventory. Personally I look after the purchase and financial planning of the company and all the other activities are taken care by respective teams.

<strong>If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do to increase their online sales, what would it be?</strong>

Any one who wants to excel and do good business on online platform must take care of these following things
<ul>
	<li>Competition: One must always keep an eye on his competitors but should never get into unhealthy competition. The bottom line is that your sales will always depend on your talent and the services that you provide to the customer.</li>
	<li>Inventory: Maintaining quality products in a large inventory is another big factor to increase online sales and gain the trust of your customers. When you have a huge inventory with a wide price range of products, it give several buying options to customers. So, your sales largely depend on your catalogue size and how well you are presenting your products to the end user.</li>
	<li>Customer satisfaction: I believe that this is the most important factor for great sales. If your first service is to a customer than you can only win as a seller - this includes delivery and packaging etc. I believe that then this customer will keep returning to you. Retaining a customer should be the prime goal in any business.</li>
</ul>
<strong>What's your advice for new sellers coming online?</strong>

My personal advice for new online sellers is that they should not come into this business with short term goals. Online business and specially platforms like <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> can do wonders for your career. The only requisite for online sales is to do HONEST business. Online selling is attractive, but it comes with a lot of responsibility with your reputation at stake.

<a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> today!

Stay in touch with us to get to know more success stories, just follow us on our Facebook pages <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Paytm-Sellers-936347589760198/timeline/?ref=bookmarks" target="_blank">Paytm Sellers</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/paytm" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and on <a href="https://twitter.com/paytm" target="_blank">Twitter</a>! We'd love to hear from you.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Always one step ahead - Learn about selling online jewelry skills from Bhavesh J Navlakha</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/always-one-step-ahead-learn-about-selling-online-jewelry-skills-from-bhavesh-j-navlakha/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Oct 2015 06:43:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=425</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="p1"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-5_-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s3">Online jewellery seller- Bhavesh J </span><span class="s1">Navlakha shares his experience of <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">selling online</a> on <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a>. He talks about his dedication and commitment to customer service which has brought immense growth.</span><span class="s4"> Bhavesh is one of the online jewellery sellers on Paytm and aims setting up new trends on the marketplace. </span><span class="s5">Learn from his experience of setting up an online </span><span class="s3">jewellery </span><span class="s5">business.</span></p>
<p class="p4"><strong><span class="s1">You're one of top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them. </span></strong></p>
<p class="p5"><span class="s1"><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=21010&amp;mn=sukkhi%20Fashion%20jewellery" target="_blank">Sukkhi</a> is now a well know brand in the world of Online Fashion Jewellery. We offer unique designer head to toe jewellery in kundan, cubic zirconia and american diamond. We have more than 2500 unique products, a well sorted variety, in the following sub-categories of Australian diamond sets, bangles, bracelets, jewellery sets, earrings, Kada, Mangalsutra pendant, Mangalsutra sets, Maangtikka, necklace sets, nose p</span>ins, pendants, pendant sets, rings and toe rings.</p>
<p class="p5"><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=21010&amp;mn=sukkhi%20Fashion%20jewellery" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-5_webpage-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="648" /></a></p>
<p class="p6"><strong><span class="s1">What got you into doing your own business? </span></strong></p>
<p class="p5"><span class="s1">When I started my business, <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">eCommerce</a> was a very new and booming industry. To be honest, I didn’t start my eCommerce business with big goals or target. It started when I decided to do something different and got into this business full hearted. But very soon my brand <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=21010&amp;mn=sukkhi%20Fashion%20jewellery" target="_blank">Sukkhi</a> got a very good response and this new journey of  <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">selling online</a> started.
</span></p>
<p class="p5"><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=21010&amp;mn=sukkhi%20Fashion%20jewellery" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-5_products-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a></p>
<p class="p6"><strong><span class="s1">How did you get into selling online and came to know about Paytm? </span></strong></p>
<p class="p5"><span class="s1">Our aim was to get onboard on all the top marketplaces. Earlier, Paytm was only offering mobile recharge and utilities billing and had very huge traffic on its website. As soon as Paytm launched its marketplace, we approached Paytm to onboard and started our successful business there.
</span><span class="s4">
</span><strong><span class="s1">What were your first challenges of selling online?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p7"><span class="s3">When we initially started our <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">online business</a> w</span><span class="s1">e were unaware of systematic procedure of the order processing, inventory management, price management and catalog management. Learning and building a strong team with the new mode of business was really a challenge for us.</span></p>
<p class="p6"><strong><span class="s1">What is your typical day like as an online seller? </span></strong></p>
<p class="p7"><span class="s1">It’s very easy to sell on <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> as there is a dedicated and supportive team to help you out as a seller. As soon as we on boarded Paytm, I received a good number of orders from the very first day.</span></p>
<strong><span class="s6">If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do  to increase their online sales, what would it be?</span></strong>
<ul class="ul1">
	<li class="li8"><span class="s1">Inventory Management: Inventory management ensures us to keep our stock up to date and never disappoints any buyer with cancellation of orders.
</span></li>
	<li class="li8"><span class="s1">Catalog Management: Descriptive and informative catalog with really good images of your products always wins the trust of buyers and increases your business.
</span></li>
	<li class="li7"><span class="s1">Backend Team: A strong backend team to process the day to day task in a systematic way without delay in any service to your buyer also helps to increase online sales. </span></li>
</ul>
<p class="p6"><strong><span class="s1">What's your advice for new sellers coming online? </span></strong></p>
<p class="p9"><span class="s1">E-commerce is a vast industry; to standout here you need to be very dedicated to this business. You should keep yourself up to date with new strategies and policies and trends of the marketplace.</span></p>
<a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Sign up on Paytm</a> today!

Stay in touch with us to get to know more success stories, just follow us on our Facebook pages <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Paytm-Sellers-936347589760198/timeline/?ref=bookmarks" target="_blank">Paytm Sellers</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/paytm" target="_blank">Paytm</a> and on <a href="https://twitter.com/paytm" target="_blank">Twitter</a>! We'd love to hear from you.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Aggressive Retailing and The Three Phases of Halloween</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/hello-world/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Oct 2015 10:04:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?p=1</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="stcpDiv">

This won’t be news to you: Halloween is a huge retail event. But—what might be surprising for some is that this doesn’t just mean increased sales in the third week of October, when half of the world scrambles to bring their spooky, adorable, or wicked clever Halloween costumes to life.

The real opportunity in this retail holiday occurs in three phases—starting right now—as millions of people come to terms with the end of summer, and embrace Back to School, warm Autumn colors, cooler weather, falling leaves—you get the picture.

And, as eBay endeavors to up the ante in terms of aggressive retailing—or marketing in line with the various phases of big retail holidays—we want to make sure you’re on board as well. In other words, we’ll be working harder to drum up the business for each phase of the big retail events, we just need you to serve up the inventory to meet this new level of demand.

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The Journey Ahead: Your Business, Our Commitment</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/my-first-blog/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Oct 2015 10:23:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?p=6</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="stcpDiv">

Take, for example, Michael Greco, who was in search of an old print ad featuring his late father.  A simple query on his social channels led him to the listing on eBay. Immediately he purchased it, and the ad now hangs in his office. “I smile at it every time I pass by it,” says Michael. “I look at it every single day.”

<a href="https://www.ebayinc.com/stories/news/treasures-hunted-my-dad-was-in-a-miller-light-ad/" target="_blank">This connection</a> – both tangible and deeply personal – was made possible because of you – our sellers. And, connections like this are made millions of times over on eBay.

I am excited to be joined this week in San Jose by more than 1,000 sellers who are connecting, discovering, learning and celebrating together at the <a href="http://pages.ebay.com/weare20/video.html" target="_blank">eBay Seller Summit</a>. As we recognize the accomplishments of building a global marketplace with 157 million active buyers and 25 million sellers, we are moving forward with changes to help your business grow.

Today, we are announcing the <a href="http://pages.ebay.com/sellerinformation/news/fallupdate2015/index.html" target="_blank">Seller Update</a>, with changes that are intended to help you make even more connections and improve your selling experience on eBay. I’m pleased that these changes directly reflect what we’ve heard from you, and they include:

</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Our Down Payment, Your Success</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/test3/</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I spent last week with our sellers, both in San Jose and across social media, celebrating eBay’s 20<sup>th</sup> anniversary at the paytm<a href="http://pages.ebay.com/weare20/video.html" target="_blank"> Seller Summit</a>. During the week we also announced our <a href="http://www.ebay.com/sellerupdate" target="_blank">fall seller update.</a> These changes mark some of the biggest steps to date on our journey to create a marketplace that truly reflects our powerful and unique seller community. I could not agree more with Devin’s quote, referenced above and featured in a recent <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-09-10/ebay-revamps-seller-rating-system-in-appeal-to-merchants" target="_blank">Bloomberg article</a>, <em>“The announcements we’re making today are a down payment on how we’re evolving the partnership with our sellers.” </em>We are listening to you, we are acting on what you’ve told us … and there is much more to be done.

At the summit, the eBay leadership team – including Jordan and myself - met with more than 1,000 sellers from around the world. We heard directly from small sellers, big sellers, new sellers and some of the <a href="https://www.ebayinc.com/stories/news/meet-the-buyer-of-the-broken-laser-pointer/" target="_blank">very first customers on our platform</a>.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How Kristie Runs Three Successful paytm Stores from “the Yaak”</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/test5/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 07 Oct 2015 16:17:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://localhost:9000/wordpress/?p=43</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Kristie hails from “the Yaak,” a rugged region in the extreme northwest corner of “Big Sky Country” Montana—right near the Canada/Idaho border. And, outside of what serves as her “listing station” is a view that would make <a href="http://www.ebay.com/bhp/ansel-adams" target="_blank">Ansel Adams</a> swoon: Lodgepole pines for miles, the rushing Yaak River bursting with trout—all framed by the majestic Purcell Mountain Range in the far distance. Whoever coined “picture-perfect,” this is what they had in mind.

However, that doesn’t tell the whole story. Not by a long shot. Check this out: The nearest post office and town with more than a tavern and mercantile is more than forty miles away, her children make up 2/3 of the town’s tiny log cabin school, and <a href="http://www.history.com/shows/mountain-men/cast/tom-oar" target="_blank">Tom Oar, star of the History Channel’s hit show “Mountain Men,"</a> lives just up the road.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Test Page</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/test-page/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Oct 2015 09:12:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=201</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/a0865e34-cd41-4a31-88df-e1b77607b1e0.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-202" src="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/a0865e34-cd41-4a31-88df-e1b77607b1e0.jpg" alt="a0865e34-cd41-4a31-88df-e1b77607b1e0" width="640" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Wikipedia is a free <a title="Encyclopedia" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Encyclopedia">encyclopedia</a>, written <a title="Collaborative editing" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collaborative_editing">collaboratively</a> by <a class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Who writes Wikipedia" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Who_writes_Wikipedia">the people who use it</a>. It is a special type of website designed to make collaboration easy, called a <a title="Wiki" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki">wiki</a>. Many people are constantly improving Wikipedia, making thousands of changes per hour. All of these changes are recorded in <a title="Help:Page history" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Page_history">article histories</a> and <a title="Help:Recent changes" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Recent_changes">recent changes</a>. For a more detailed account of the project, see <b><a title="Wikipedia:About" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:About">About Wikipedia</a></b>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><big><b>How you can contribute</b></big></p>

<div class="thumb tright" style="text-align: justify;">
<div class="thumbinner">
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"></div>
Click "Edit" to change an article

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright" style="text-align: justify;">
<div class="thumbinner">
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"></div>
Editing tutorial for Wikipedia

</div>
</div>
</div>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><b>Don't be afraid to edit</b> – <i>anyone</i> can edit almost every page, and we are encouraged to <b><a title="Wikipedia:Be bold" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Be_bold">be bold</a></b>! Find something that can be improved and make it better—for example, spelling, grammar, rewriting for readability, adding content, or removing non-constructive edits. If you wish to add new facts, please try to provide <a title="Help:Introduction to referencing/1" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1">references</a> so they may be <a title="Wikipedia:Verifiability" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability">verified</a>, or suggest them on the article's <a title="Help:Introduction to talk pages" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_talk_pages">discussion page</a>. Changes to controversial topics and Wikipedia's main pages should usually be discussed first. <b><a title="Wikipedia:Contributing to Wikipedia" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Contributing_to_Wikipedia">Contributing to Wikipedia</a></b> will provide you with resources on all the basics needed to use, comment on, and contribute to Wikipedia.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Remember – you can't break Wikipedia; all edits can be reversed, fixed or improved later. Wikipedia is <a title="Wikipedia:Editing policy" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Editing_policy">allowed to be imperfect</a>. So go ahead, edit an article and help make Wikipedia the best information source on the Internet!</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><b>Donate</b> – Wikipedia is free to use, but relies on donations and grants to do so. Please consider donating using the <b>Donate to Wikipedia</b> link on the left to help with the project's running costs and expansion.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Online Marketplace 101</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/online-marketplace-101/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2015 14:03:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[paytmadmin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/?p=350</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/online-marketplace.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-351" src="http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/online-marketplace.jpg" alt="online-marketplace" width="748" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">What is an Online Marketplace?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Fundamentally, a marketplace is a multisided platform, which connects two or more groups. A mall is a two-sided marketplace as it on one hand provides basic amenities to sellers for opening a store and on the other attracts the customers who eventually end up transacting with these sellers. Android is a three-sided marketplace as it forms a triangular transacting relation between app developers, phone manufacturers and end users. A smartphone can be classified as a four-sided platform since it builds interaction between the service providers, app developers, value added service providers and the end customers. In a similar manner, an online marketplace is a platform, which connects a seller and a buyer in the virtual space.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">What are the Key Attributes of an Online Marketplaces?</p>

<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li>Neutral: Online marketplaces never discriminates one set of users, on either side, against the others. At the same time, they are usually highly meritocratic thereby handsomely rewarding the best players or users.</li>
	<li>Cross Network Effect: Addition of new members on one side increases the value of the marketplace for the members on the other side.</li>
	<li>Secure: They provide a secure transacting platform for al the interacting groups. They instill confidence among the users and this happens to be one of the main reasons of their existence.</li>
	<li>New Opportunities: They end up creating new opportunities since they initiate interactions which otherwise wouldn’t have taken place</li>
	<li>Zero Marginal Cost: Since the main value creation comes from the interaction between groups, so once matured, the marketplaces operate on zero marginal costs. This however does not mean that they do not have any fixed costs.</li>
	<li>Scalable: They represent one of the most scalable ecosystems which can transcend national boundaries and cultural barriers.</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Why is Paytm a unique marketplace?</p>

<ol style="text-align: justify;">
	<li>Owing to its merchant base reaching the figure of 1lakh and a customer base of more than 100 million, strong cross network effects are in operation.</li>
	<li>Cashbacks being offered into the customer’s Paytm Wallet increases the stickiness of the customer base on Paytm platform.</li>
	<li>A complete Do It Yourself (DIY) seller panel at Paytm, increases the usability of the platform from the sellers end.</li>
	<li>Shortest seller payout cycle makes the platform more profitable for the sellers.</li>
	<li>Paytm treats big and small sellers alike thereby operating as an equal opportunity platform.</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">According to some of the industry experts, Paytm is expected to become the largest Online Marketplace of India owing to the synergies it shares with  other products like Paytm Wallet, payment gateway etc. We sincerely hope and look forward to share this success journey with all our sellers.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Getting paid on Paytm</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/getting-paid-on-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Oct 2015 06:58:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=340</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm is proud to offers its sellers the fastest payment cycle in the marketplace and for the ease of sellers’ we have adopted twice a  week payment cycle for the sales done by them.You receive a payment email from Paytm once your dispatched order show  'Delivered' status in the system.The PDF invoices (after deducting sum of marketplace commission+ Payment gateway + Logistics (LMD partner) + penalty if any) along with the orders/payouts is e-mailed to you and the funds are transferred in your bank account. However, the banks normally  take 2-3 days for these funds to reflect in your account.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">You have complete access and can view all detailed orders and earnings for products in the </span><b>Payment</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> tab by logging into the </span><b><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/#/" target="_blank">Seller Panel</a></b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The Payment tab lists details pertaining to Payment Dashboard, All payments, Unpaid Orders and All Order details.</span>
<ol>
	<li><b>Payment Dashboard</b> : Payment Dashboard gives you the  view of date wise break up of your payments.</li>
	<li><b>All Payments</b>: This tab gives an insight to all your earnings, deductions or penalties.  You can view the payment break up by clicking on 'View Payment Details' in this tab. By clicking on 'View Orders' the seller can check for any deductions on his orders if any and enables you to download Order CSV file to check for orders.</li>
	<li><b>Unpaid Orders</b>: This tab has a detailed list of all the unpaid orders and allows you to download <b>Order CSV </b>file . Sellers can easily access and view logistic and marketplace fee here and any deductions that he would have to bear for certain product refunds.</li>
	<li><b>All Orders</b>:The last tab in Payments is <b>All Orders</b> where you can view all the orders payout with their complete status.</li>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">You are always welcome to ask a question or to get a solution of your query on Payments. We are alway reachable at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><b>merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</b></a><b>.</b>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Anyone can sell online - In conversation with a top online luxury watch seller</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/anyone-can-sell-online-in-conversation-with-a-top-online-luxury-watch-seller/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Oct 2015 10:04:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=431</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-story-6_blog-post_5-10-15.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-445" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-story-6_blog-post_5-10-15.jpg" alt="Seller-story-6_blog-post_5-10-15" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the best things you can do to help become <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">successful selling online</a> is to study the most successful sellers and see what they are doing.  Successful online sellers come from many different backgrounds and they might sell something completely different from your business. Nonetheless the learning that you will gain, will help you <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">grow your business</a>.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Raj Kumar Tarani from <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=20529&amp;mn=AirNet%20India" target="_blank">AirNet</a> is selling luxury watches at the click of a button. We caught up with him to hear more about his tips for online sellers. Here’s what he has to say.</span>

<b>You're one of top online sellers - what kind of products do you sell? Tell us about them.</b>

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=20529&amp;mn=AirNet%20India" target="_blank">AirNet</a> is selling products across fashion, electronics / mobile and appliances category. But our major forte is watches segment with multiple brands.

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=20529&amp;mn=AirNet%20India" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-6_webpage-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="648" /></a>

<b>What got you into doing your own business?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The success stories of Indian entrepreneurs like Vijay Sehkar Sharma, Kunal Bahl, Sachin Bansal and their likes, their vision and ability to drive business. The speed inspired me to turn into entrepreneurship. I felt that I can create success story myself with <a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=20529&amp;mn=AirNet%20India" target="_blank">AirNet</a> using the technology businesses get from <a href="https://paytm.com" target="_blank">online marketplaces</a>.</span>

<a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?merchant=20529&amp;mn=AirNet%20India" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/09/Seller-story-6_products-blog-post_25-9-15.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="298" /></a>

<strong><span class="s1">How did you get into selling online and came to know about Paytm?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We were already working with many marketplaces. First we were a bit sceptical about a recharge company getting into <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">eCommerce</a> and we were carefully entering the platform, but were amazed at the speed at which operations were scaled up by <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Paytm</a>’s team. This did benefit us as a seller.</span>

<strong><span class="s1">What were your first challenges of selling online?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Inventory management of large portfolio with multiple portals to cater to, and handling large inflow of payments in our account were quite a challenge for us at AirNet.</span>

<strong><span class="s1">What is your typical day like as an online seller?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">That’s quite simple to say - ensure flawless and timely deliveries and improving of customer delight. The customer is our priority. Also of course we want to grow continuously and focus on improving and enhancing business volumes with <a href="https://paytm.com" target="_blank">Paytm</a>.  </span>

<strong><span class="s6">If you had to pick 3 things that every person simply MUST do  to increase their online sales, what would it be?</span></strong>
<ol>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Continuous focus on inventory and prices: Track your inventory properly and calculate it well. This is not only helpful for better serving customers, but also for tax purposes.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Correct Cataloging, with selection of right keywords: The products you are selling are part of your business identity and are what sets you apart from others. Make it a point to organize it well and highlight your best offerings. Further every sales begins with a keyword search. Your job is to make sure that the expected keywords by customers are related to your products. You have to include the right ones in your product description. Remember, the first step to stand out is to be seen / found by your customers.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Improving on delivery operations to minimize returns: The ability to quickly and accurately fulfill customers online orders is a task you have to take serious. Streamline functions, set up process that help you serve customers efficiently.</span></li>
</ol>
<strong><span class="s1">What's your advice for new sellers coming online?</span></strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Don’t Look for shortcuts, be genuine and authentic. Always respect your customers, as well as the <a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">online marketplace</a> policies.</span>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Boost online sales with perfect ratings!</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/boost-online-sales-with-perfect-ratings/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Oct 2015 06:04:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=438</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">The power of seller ratings on any marketplace is enormous, as your customers trust online reviews and consider the ratings/reviews as personal recommendations. You must target for good ratings as it helps you in following ways:</span>
<ul>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">High ratings increase your sales &amp; identify you as a trusted seller</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Helps give more visibility to your product</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">High rating means people trust you and prefer to buy from you</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">The seller ratings on <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm</a> marketplace are a great way to speak for your performance, ranking and the services you give for your products. In today's eCommerce world, we cannot ignore the vast influence of internet shoppers as our customers refer and trust seller ratings before placing an order. Currently,   on Paytm a customer can rate you on three aspects :-</span>
<ol>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product as described</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product Packaging and Handling</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Timely Delivery</span></li>
</ol>
<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-rating_blog-post_1-10-15.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-439" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/Seller-rating_blog-post_1-10-15.jpg" alt="Seller-rating_blog-post_1-10-15" width="659" height="274" /></a>

<b>#Ways to improve rating</b>
<ul>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Product description- Give true and genuine description of the product.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Packaging and Handling- Adhere to Paytm packaging guidelines. Ensure to pack and ship every order with utmost care to avoid any damage or breakage while handling. You can learn more about detailed </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/#/trainingCentre"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paytm’s packaging guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for each category on Seller Panel.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Timely delivery- Make sure to deliver an order on time.Check that </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">you are packing and getting orders ready for shipment within 24 hours - This will help boost your overall average ratings. </span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quality-You must ensure shipping best quality products to ensure reduced returns from customers.  To achieve this, use great quality images, give accurate product description and ship the exact product that you have displayed on the marketplace. </span></li>
</ul>
<b>#Things to avoid</b>
<ul>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not sell fake </span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not give false description of products</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not ship wrong product other than what is shown to the buyer on the Paytm website Make sure you do not ship used, faulty and re-furbished products</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not give false description in product’s attributes like size and colour</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not forget to send freebies</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">and other offers that you promised with the main product</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case you require any help/advice relating to rating, please feel free to mail us at </span><a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">   </span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Learn how  Promotions and Campaigns work at Paytm</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/learn-how-promotions-and-campaigns-work-at-paytm/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 12 Oct 2015 12:10:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=462</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Sales and Promotions</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We at Paytm are dedicated towards increasing engagement of merchants to boost-up their sales. We roll out promotions from time-to-time to facilitate increased business for our merchants. The promotions may be category specific or generic in nature.   </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Below are some of the frequently asked questions which will help you understand better about the campaign process.</span>

<strong>#How can I participate?</strong>

If merchants are shortlisted for any upcoming campaign, they will receive an invitation e-mail from our end, asking their participation. They might be requested to share the list of products they wish to participate with. The list is screened at our end and a final communication is sent out to merchants if their products (partially/completely) qualify for the promotion.

<strong>#How will the campaign be beneficial for merchants?</strong>

We try to boost the sales  by providing extra cashback to the customers, free shipping charges etc. Through the campaign, the products will receive better visibility on the Paytm website/app.

<strong>#How much discount should merchants need to give on their products?</strong>

Based on the campaign, merchants will receive needful details along with our participation invite e-mail clearly stating the discounts and other incentives that they will need to give on their products.

<strong>#What will be the structure of commissions and logistics?</strong>

Standard charges for commissions and logistics will apply. In case of any changes in the same, the detailed structure will be provided in the invitation e-mail.

<strong>#How much does Paytm charge for promotions ?</strong>
Paytm offers several properties (locations &amp; spots on the App &amp; website) which may be utilized by the sellers for promoting their brand / products. The details about these properties can be found in the image below:-

#How much does Paytm charge for promotions ?
Paytm offers several properties (locations &amp; spots on the App &amp; website) which may be utilized by the sellers for promoting their brand / products. The details about these properties can be found in the image below:-

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The cost of these promotions depends upon your product category and the location / spot you chose for promotion. The rates are calculated based upon the number of visitors who are expected to view / click and thus may vary from time to time. <b>#How to boost up your sales?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To boost up your sales, we strongly advice you to </span>
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Participate in as many as promotions rolled out by Paytm</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep the specifics of the products: Selling Price (SP), Market Retail Price (MRP), Discounts etc. in sync with the requirements of the campaign</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Update your catalog with more products and keep proper inventory levels </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Try to provide competitive prices on your products especially during promotion</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always remember to follow packaging guidelines and ship orders as per SLA</span></li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Increase your online sales with an effective catalog</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/increase-your-online-sales-with-an-effective-catalog/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 06:26:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=504</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Catalog plays a significant role in advertising your products on <a href="https://paytm.com/" target="_blank">Paytm marketplace</a> that helps customers to buy from you. As a successful seller, you must be able to convince buyers that you sell the right product,  and this is achieved with the right catalog that  describes and tells your customers about your products. Let’s see what information should your catalog have.

Your catalog should include all required information about the product that you sell. This helps customers in an informed purchase decision. A catalog page, also called the Product Details page, typically  should include:
<ol>
	<li>Product Name</li>
	<li>Product Description</li>
	<li>Product Attributes</li>
</ol>
<b>Product name:</b>

You product’s name is the most critical element of your catalog as it directly determines how many views your product will receive. After images, an informative product name plays a vital role in grabbing the interest of your potential customers. Typically, a product page looks like

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/heading-circle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-505" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/heading-circle.jpg" alt="heading-circle" width="408" height="312" /></a>and should include the following components:
<table style="height: 265px;" width="826">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="118"></td>
<td width="453">         Components of Product Name</td>
<td width="319">Examples</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="118">Brand</td>
<td width="453">Always mention the name of the brand or the designer in the beginning.</td>
<td width="319">Nike, Levi’s, HP, Samsung</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="118">Model Number/Name</td>
<td width="453">You must mention the accurate model number or name in the product name, especially for electronics.</td>
<td width="319">Nike Air Zoom Structure 19, Levi's 2 Horse Tee,
Dell Inspiron 15 3542 Notebook,
Samsung Galaxy S6 Edge</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="118">Colour</td>
<td width="453">Include the colour of the product .</td>
<td width="319">Levi's White Cotton Shirt</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="118">Product Type</td>
<td width="453">Always Include the type or leaf category of the product.</td>
<td width="319">Running shoes, casual t-shirt, gaming laptop, smart phone</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;

While adding a product name, you should follow the below guidelines.
<ol>
	<li>Do not make use of misleading keywords that do not speak for your product. For example when describing Apple iPhone 5S 32 GB - Do not write Apple smartphone Apple iPhone 5S 32 GB.</li>
	<li>Do not stuff keywords. For Apple iPhone 5S ,  say Apple iPhone 5S 32GB and not Apple iPhone- iPhone 5S 32 GB.</li>
	<li>Do not use special characters(^, ~, ™,¥, ©,®,») , punctuation marks(!,. : ; ‘’ ‘?) or asterisks (*) as this would affect low visibility in search results</li>
	<li>Always check for grammar and do a spell check.</li>
	<li>Avoid using acronyms or abbreviations (For example write Hewlett-Packard and not HP) as many customers will not understand this.</li>
	<li>Do not use “100% genuine” or “Original” words in product title.</li>
	<li>Always follow searchable keyword that describe your product truly.For example use iphone and not Apple smartphone.</li>
	<li>Be sure to use the correct spellings, always use title case that is the first letter of  each word should be in uppercase. For example Red Cotton<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span><a href="https://paytm.com/@adidas" target="_blank">Addidas<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></a>T-shirt.</li>
</ol>
#<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span><b>Product Description</b>

Here you describe your product in details .This information helps customer learn more about the product and has details that help you sell your products. Product description is your opportunity to provide more information about your product.  A powerful product description should summarize:
<ul>
	<li>Why your customer should buy the product</li>
	<li>The key features of the product in case of electronics</li>
	<li>Different uses and benefits</li>
	<li>Suggested occasions and size guide in case of apparels and footwear</li>
	<li>Warranty details of the products in case of electronics and home appliances</li>
	<li>Additional attributes that are not listed under mandatory or optional fields.</li>
</ul>
<b>Tip</b>: After adding the content and attributes in the product description section (in<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span><a href="https://seller.paytm.com/login" target="_blank">Seller Panel</a>), always preview it to check how this section will look on the website.

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/description-circle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/description-circle.jpg" alt="description-circle" width="408" height="312" /></a>

While adding a product description, you should follow the below guidelines.
<ol>
	<li>Do not use misleading information that is not related to your product</li>
	<li>Do not use long descriptions as it is unlikely that customers would go through them</li>
	<li>Do not use negative sentences to get a customer’s attention</li>
	<li>Do not copy description from other products on Paytm or other eCommerce websites</li>
	<li>Use searchable and relevant keywords  for relevant results of your customers</li>
	<li>Use simple and clear language</li>
	<li>Use correct spellings as typing errors are not search engine optimized.</li>
	<li>Always use sentence case. The first letter of a sentence should be in uppercase. For example, Make a distinct style statement wearing this red  shirt from<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span><a href="https://paytm.com/shop/search/?q=colorPlus&amp;from=organic&amp;brand=17487" target="_blank">ColorPlus</a></li>
	<li>Use multiple product description to describe each product of your product</li>
	<li>Use bullet point to help your customer read easily</li>
</ol>
<b>#Product attributes</b>

This lists mandatory and optional fields and should always feature accurate attributes . Product attributes is the section where detailed features of your products need to be mentioned. This is the section that helps customers find your product and informs them about your product . Therefore, you should add as many attributes as possible.

Our Product Detail page and catalog templates have been divided into two parts for attributes:
<ul>
	<li>Mandatory attribute fields</li>
	<li>Optional attribute fields</li>
	<li>The below image lists attribute that you can add to your product.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Learn all about Return Processing Centre(RPC) to manage return items</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/learn-all-about-return-processing-centrerpc-to-manage-return-items/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Oct 2015 09:25:21 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=513</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We are happy to announce the launch of our new policy around customer returns with <b>Return Processing Centre(RPC)</b>.<b> </b>Now, items returned by the customers will be sent to Paytm’s Return Processing Centre for quality check before sending them back to the merchant. With this managing customer returns will become much easier.

Below are some of the most frequently asked questions around Return Processing Centre which will help you understand this process in detail.

<b>What is RPC?</b>

A Returns Processing Center is a physical hub where the merchandise returned by the customer is brought for quality check before it is dispatched further to the merchant.

As per the new Paytm policy, items that are returned by a customer will be sent to Paytm’s Returns Processing Center (RPC).

The products will be quality checked against the customer's complaint and if the customer's complaint is validated, the product will be sent back to the seller and debit would be marked to the seller's account.

If Paytm feels that the products received at the RPC are not in a condition to be sent back to the seller, the product will not be sent back to the seller and NO debit will be marked to the seller's account.

Paytm's decision, in either case, shall be treated as final.
<h2></h2>
<b> #How do I know if my shipment will go to the RPC?</b>

It is Paytm’s prerogative to decide which shipments will go through the RPC. If your shipment is assigned to the RPC, you will get the following content in your email with ‘Yes’ mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column:

“This is to inform you that as per our logistics partner’s report, following items have been picked from the customer for return. Please find below summary of the picked items.”

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-1_-blogpost-27-10-15.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-521" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-1_-blogpost-27-10-15.jpg" alt="table-1_-blogpost-27-10-15" width="659" height="97" /></a>If ‘No’ is mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column, then that particular shipment will not go through the RPC. Such shipments will be sent directly to the seller's address.

A ‘RPC Assigned’ flag will also be visible to the seller on the Seller Panel if the shipment is assigned to the RPC.

<strong>#How much time will be taken by the RPC for QC?</strong>

At RPC, every item will be quality checked thoroughly to validate customer complaint. The RPC will take a maximum of 72 hours to process the shipments.
<strong>#What if my item is ‘QC failed’ at RPC?</strong>

‘QC failed or QC rejected’ implies that Paytm felt that the product was not in a condition to be sent back to the seller.

If the item is QC failed at RPC, we will not send the item back you and the item will be liquidated from the RPC. The status of such items will be shown as ‘Liquidated’ in the ‘Returns’ tab of Seller Panel. No debit will be marked to you in such cases.

The following communication shall be received by you in this case:

“We have found that the following product that was returned by the customer, was not in a condition to be sent back to you and hence is being retained by Paytm. No debit will be marked to your account for this product”

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-2_-blogpost-27-10-15.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-522" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-2_-blogpost-27-10-15.jpg" alt="table-2_-blogpost-27-10-15" width="659" height="129" /></a><b></b>

<b>#What if my item is ‘QC passed’ at RPC?</b>

‘QC passed or QC accepted’ implies that the customer’s complaint was genuine. Such shipments will be sent back to you and shipping details of such shipments will be communicated to you once the shipments are dispatched from the RPC.

A debit will be marked to your account in such cases once the shipment is delivered and the following communication will be sent to you in this case:

“The following items returned by the customer have been quality checked at RPC. We have found that the customer's complaint was valid and hence the product is being sent back to you”.

<a href="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-3_-blogpost-27-10-151.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-524" src="http://paytm.com/sellers/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/10/table-3_-blogpost-27-10-151.jpg" alt="table-3_-blogpost-27-10-15" width="659" height="132" /></a>

<b>#What if I want my shipment to be assigned to an RPC?</b>

The prerogative of mapping a seller to the RPC/sending a shipment to the RPC shall lie with Paytm. You can raise a request to process your shipments through the RPC via merchant helpdesk (email: <a href="mailto:merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com">merchant.helpdesk@paytm.com</a>) but Paytm’s decision in this regard shall remain final.

<b>#When will I receive my product if it is QC passed?</b>

Once the Item has passed the quality check and has been shipped from RPC, you will get a notification about the shipments dispatched through an email. you should receive such item(s) at your warehouse within 21 days of reverse pickup from the customer.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Learn all about Return Processing Centre (RPC) to manage return items</title>
		<link>http://180.151.101.114:9000/wordpress/index.php/learn-all-about-return-processing-centre-rpc-to-manage-return-items/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Oct 2015 06:11:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ashsingla]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://paytm.com/sellers/?p=511</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We are happy to announce the launch of our new policy around customer returns with <b>Return Processing Centre(RPC).</b>Now, items returned by the customers will be sent to Paytm’s Return Processing Centre for quality check before sending them back to the merchant. With this managing customer returns will become much easier.

Below are some of the most frequently asked questions around Return Processing Centre which will help you understand this process in detail.

<b>What is RPC?</b>

A Returns Processing Center is a physical hub where the merchandise returned by the customer is brought for quality check before it is dispatched further to the merchant.

As per the new Paytm policy, items that are returned by a customer will be sent to Paytm’s Returns Processing Center (RPC).

The products will be quality checked against the customer's complaint and if the customer's complaint is validated, the product will be sent back to the seller and debit would be marked to the seller's account.

If Paytm feels that the products received at the RPC are not in a condition to be sent back to the seller, the product will not be sent back to the seller and NO debit will be marked to the seller's account.

Paytm's decision, in either case, shall be treated as final.
<h2><b>#How do I know if my shipment will go to the RPC?</b></h2>
It is Paytm’s prerogative to decide which shipments will go through the RPC. If your shipment is assigned to the RPC, you will get the following content in your email with ‘Yes’ mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column:

“This is to inform you that as per our logistics partner’s report, following items have been picked from the customer for return. Please find below summary of the picked items.”
<table style="height: 88px" width="822">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><b>REVERSE COURIER</b></td>
<td><b>AWB NO</b></td>
<td><b>ORDER NO</b></td>
<td><b>ITEM ID</b></td>
<td><b>ITEM NAME</b></td>
<td><b>QUANTITY</b></td>
<td><b>PICKED DATE</b></td>
<td><b>RPC ASSIGNED
</b></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
&nbsp;

If ‘No’ is mentioned under the ‘RPC Assigned’ column, then that particular shipment will not go through the RPC. Such shipments will be sent directly to the seller's address.

A ‘RPC Assigned’ flag will also be visible to the seller on the Seller Panel if the shipment is assigned to the RPC.
<h2><b>#How much time will be taken by the RPC for QC?</b></h2>
At RPC, every item will be quality checked thoroughly to validate customer complaint. The RPC will take a maximum of <b>72 hours</b> to process the shipments.
<h2><b>#What if my item is ‘QC failed’ at RPC?</b></h2>
‘QC failed or QC rejected’ implies that Paytm felt that the product was not in a condition to be sent back to the seller.

If the item is QC failed at RPC, we will not send the item back you and the item will be liquidated from the RPC. The status of such items will be shown as ‘Liquidated’ in the ‘Returns’ tab of Seller Panel. No debit will be marked to you in such cases.

The following communication shall be received by you in this case:

“We have found that the following product that was returned by the customer, was not in a condition to be sent back to you and hence is being retained by Paytm. No debit will be marked to your account for this product”

<tbody>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>]]></content:encoded>
